title: strawberry onion salad
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, onion juice and vinegar together. Slowly add oil to blend.
Add poppy seeds.	Refrigerate overnight.

title: tutti-frutti lemon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine undrained canned fruits with flaked coconut and lemon juice. Sprinkle the instant lemon pudding mix over the mixture and toss lightly to combine.
Chill.

title: kid's favorite chicken
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, cheese, salt, garlic and pepper; set aside.
Cut chicken into small pieces (about 1 1/2 inches).
Dip chicken in margarine, then into crumb mixture.
Place on a baking sheet in a single layer.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Serve with Pineapple Dipping Sauce.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans and cook in large pan.
After about an hour, add sausage.
When beans are done and just slightly thickened, add rice and cook until rice is tender.
Be sure to add water and salt as needed.
These are great with Mexican corn bread.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 15 minutes. Beat softened cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk. Fold into Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Prepare pudding. Pour over cream cheese layer. Chill several hours. Spread Cool Whip over pudding.

title: ranch rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 1 quart casserole for 1 hour.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: freezer corn
directions: Put all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool a little, then put into bags.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage together with pepper and onion in skillet; drain fat and add both sugars, beans, catsup, liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce. Put in casserole dish and heat about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 300 for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, peanut butter and sweetener; blend well.
Add milk.
Combine with egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, blending well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water. Bake 10 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine cooked chicken with soup and broth, heat to boiling. Grease a 2 quart casserole, put in chicken mixture, add sliced eggs.
Make a mixture of the oleo, flour, pepper and milk; stir or mix until mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture over chicken and eggs. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: labor day marinated salad
directions: Cut and mix in large bowl.
Pour Italian (Wish-Bone) dressing over vegetables.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.

title: toffee
directions: Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in and spread evenly a cup of chopped nuts.
In a saucepan, let butter and brown sugar boil for 7 minutes.
Pour over nuts in pan and top with a few chocolate chips and nuts.
Press down firmly with a piece of foil.
Chill and break into chunks.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat on medium, egg yolks, sugar, flour, vanilla, milk and butter.
Pour into one unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until done.

title: chinese lemon chicken
directions: Combine dry lemon gelatin, garlic salt and mustard.
Add melted margarine; mix well.
Place gelatin mixture in oblong dish; arrange chicken in single layers, turning to coat both sides. Sprinkle with almond slices.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting once.
Remove cover; baste again and bake 15 minutes more or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a shallow dish and stir well. Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet.
Add steak to marinade, turning to coat both sides.
Cover dish and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove steak from marinade; drain well. Grill steak over medium coals 6 to 7 minutes on each side or to desired doneness.
Slice into thin slices.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar. Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add pineapple, cranberries, apples, grapes and nut mixture.
Pour into mold or Tupperware.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Assemble mixer.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter at setting #4. Gradually add sugar and continue to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve baking soda in sour milk.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with sour milk.
Add jam, mixing until thoroughly combined.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: country butter(without a cow)
directions: Have
oleo and cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend all ingredients
with
electric mixer.	Blend until smooth and creamy. Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Melt chocolate morsels, condensed milk, 1 Tbsp. butter and 1/4 tsp. salt over boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Set aside.
Sift flour, soda and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Cream 1/2 cup butter, gradually add brown sugar. Add egg and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients and oatmeal. Press 2/3 of mixture in greased 9 x 9 pan, spread with chocolate filling.
Crumble remaining mixture over filling.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: puff pudding
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and lemon peel in a large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in milk, cereal, flour and lemon juice (mixture will look curdled).
Gently stir in egg whites.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top is golden brown and begins to pull away from sides of dish.
Serve warm or cold.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and return to pan.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Now stir in remaining four ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake uncovered for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: taco casserole
directions: *Substitute 1 pound ground meat for refried beans, if desired.

title: delicious dove
directions: Pour oil in skillet and heat.
Brown doves at medium temperature for about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet and place in casserole.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and jello until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring.
Pour in pie shell.
Fill with strawberries.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: tonkatsu - pork cutlets
directions: Slice pork tenderloins into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Coat with flour. Dip in beaten eggs and dredge lightly in panko.
Deep fry in hot oil until
golden brown.
Garnish with finely shredded cabbage.
Serve with Tonkatsu Sauce.

title: zouppa firenze(soup florence)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 1/2 hour, then add spinach and cook for 1/2 hour.
For the last 10 minutes, add angel hair pasta cut in half.
Shake grated Parmesan cheese over the bowl; add red hot pepper, if desired.

title: reese peanut butter bars
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and spread in large oblong dish. Melt chocolate chips and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill until set.

title: quick nut fudge frosting
directions: Mix and beat until smooth.

title: better than sex potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour melted butter over in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes over.
Bake 1/2 hour more.

title: lima-bacon bake
directions: Cook limas in 1 1/2 cups boiling salted water 15 minutes. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Fry bacon until about half cooked.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep 3 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and celery in bacon fat until soft.
Toss together lima beans, onion, celery, cheese, pepper, Worcestershire and liquid from beans.
Bake in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 25 minutes or until browned.

title: brownie hearts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with foil, extending over edges to form handles.
Grease foil.
Cook chocolate and margarine in large microwave-safe bowl on High (100% power) for 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts until well blended.
Spread in prepared pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake. Cool in pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes for easier cutting.
Lift brownies out of pan with foil handles.
Invert onto back of pan.

title: peach blush wine cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: steve's fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, combine the first 3 ingredients.
In a large mixing bowl, mix chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme. Cook sugar mixture in pan until soft ball stage. (To
tell when you have come to this stage, let a few drops fall
from spoon into a 1-cup glass measure half filled with cold
water.
Drop will form soft balls, round in shape, when ready.)
Remove pan from heat and pour syrup mixture over chips and Marshmallow Creme in bowl.
Mix together gently, but thoroughly.
(Nuts may be added at this time, if desired, 1 or 2 cups.)
The fudge thickens quickly. Pour onto marble slab or pour into a foil-lined pan.
Let cool.

title: mock chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Mix with soups and 2/3 chow mein noodles.
Put remainder of noodles on top of casserole. If desired, mix medium stalk celery, cut and cook in small amount of water for about 15 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: this 'n that casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with grated cheese for 5 minutes before removing from oven.

title: beer pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Mix Bisquick and beer until thoroughly moistened.
Spread batter in pan.
Spread sauce carefully over batter.
Top with sausage mixture and remaining ingredients.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: black olive pate
directions: Combine cream cheese and black olives in a food processor and pure.
The mixture should be processed until it is a smooth light brown consistency.
(There should be no lumps.)
Add garlic powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with small Melba toast or small toasted fresh bread.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; stir into banana mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Pare potatoes and cook until soft.
Mash until creamy.
Work out on board with flour, salt and eggs.
Drop by spoonfuls into salt water; bring to a boil and drain.
Place on large platter and pour bread crumbs over potatoes.

title: kah lua
directions: You will need 1/2 gallon jar with wide mouth.
Bring sugar, water and coffee to a boil.
Let stand until cool.
Pour into sterilized jar and add vodka & vanilla.
Allow to stand for 2 weeks in a dark place.
Put into brown paper bag.
Stir or shake the jar at least daily.
Remove vanilla bean from bottle and serve as desired.

title: chicken salad and bacon
directions: Tear the lettuce into pieces and place in a salad bowl.
Add the next 4 ingredients and toss.
Top with eggs and bacon.
Mix together the last 4 ingredients and serve with the salad.

title: frosted pecans(you can't eat just one!)
directions: Combine first four ingredients in
saucepan over medium heat. Stir and mix well.
Bring mixture to rolling boil until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from
heat.
Add
vanilla and pecans.
Stir
well to coat pecans.
Empty
onto
cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Use fork to break apart in clusters.

title: carrot salad
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water; drain and cool.
Do not overcook.
(I sometimes use 3 cans of carrots.) Slice onion and pepper and add to cold carrots.
Combine all other ingredients and heat; do not boil.
Pour over carrots.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: orange frosty
directions: Mix all ingredients on high speed in blender.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash peeled avocado in bowl with fork.
Beat in sour cream until fluffy.
Mix in onion, salt, lemon juice, garlic and cumin. Serve right away as dip or on nachos.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator to store.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Spray a 9-inch square pan
with Mazola spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In a medium bowl, mix egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until smooth. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan or on wire rack.
If desired, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix thoroughly.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Place casserole in pan filled 1 inch deep with hot water.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 65 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge of dish comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey-mustard pork tenderloin
directions: Place tenderloins on a rack coated with cooking spray; place rack in broiler pan and set aside.
Combine honey and remaining ingredients; spoon 1/3 of honey mixture over tenderloins.
Set remaining honey mixture aside.
Bake tenderloins at 350° for 30 minutes or until meat thermometer inserted in thickest portion registers 160°, basting occasionally with remaining honey mixture. Cut tenderloins into thin slices.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut into small bites.
Slice water chestnuts.
Crush crackers in bottom of baking dish.
Mix chicken, chestnuts, soup and sour cream.
Pour mixture in the baking dish lined with crackers.
Sprinkle margarine over top.
Serves a large family.

title: quiche
directions: Mix pie dough and line 9-inch pie pan.
Cover dough with butter.
Divide 1/2 pound of bacon; make layers of bacon, vegetables and cheese.
Cover with mixed cream, pepper, sugar, milk, salt and eggs; top with rest of bacon and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° for 30 minutes.

title: sparkling lemon-lime sorbet
directions: In medium saucepan, mix gelatine with sugar.
Blend in water. Let stand for 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Let cool to room temperature.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch baking pan.
Freeze for 3 hours or until firm.
With electric mixer, beat mixture until smooth.
Return to pan; freeze 2 hours or until firm.
To serve, let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until slightly softened.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: white trash
directions: Mix raisins, cereal and peanuts together; set aside.
Combine butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter in a double boiler. Heat until the ingredients are melted.
Pour over dry ingredients and toss until well coated.
Pour powdered sugar over mixture and shake until well coated.

title: almond-apricot macaroons(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Line a cookie sheet with parchment paper and dust 2 tablespoons cake flour. Place almonds in food chopper. Pulse 3 to 5 times. Lightly spoon 3/4 cup cake flour. Pulse 3 to 4 times until coarsely blended. Place sugar, orange rind and almond extract. Pulse until mixed. Add eggs. Pulse until well mixed. Add chopped apricots. Pulse 3 to 4 times or until blended. Pour mixture on floured sheet of paper. Roll into 32 small balls or 16 large balls. Pinch top of balls like a pear. Cook at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown. Cool on wire rack.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place ground beef, salt and pepper to taste in bottom of casserole dish. Spread ketchup over this.
Spread macaroni over this, pepper, tomatoes, peas, potatoes, onion and salt and pepper on top. Cover with foil and cook at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread and pat crescent rolls onto 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake according to directions, until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: husband's choice
directions: Mix well.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart greased ring pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil zucchini and pineapple 6 minutes.
Add sugar and bring to a boil, again for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and jello.
Stir very well.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pint jars.

title: mexican fideos
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add spaghetti, onion and garlic. Cook and stir until spaghetti is browned.
Stir in tomatoes, water, chilies, salt and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer covered until liquid is absorbed and spaghetti is tender, about 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth and shape into a ball. Wrap and refrigerate.

title: chopped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in chipped beef, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well and stir in sour cream.
Spoon into shallow baking dish; sprinkle top with walnuts.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with chips or crackers.

title: barbecue ham
directions: In medium pan add ham.
Cover with water.
Bring to boil; strain.
Add all ingredients and cook over medium heat until boiling, then turn down heat to low and cook for about 1 hour.

title: sheath cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Combine cocoa, water, margarine and shortening.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add to flour mixture. Dissolve soda and buttermilk.
Add with eggs, cinnamon and vanilla to batter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: To make topping combine cream of chicken soup, half and half, sour cream, and cheese. Pour over top of tortillas. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cheese topping is cooked into tortillas.

title: chicken casserole(microwave)
directions: Put everything in a covered 2 quart dish or bowl; microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir and microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir and microwave on High for another 4 minutes.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter; put 1 can of onion rings on top.
Microwave on High for 1 minute, uncovered.

title: potato casserole
directions: Can use corn flakes or croutons as a topping, but not necessary.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer 20 minutes.
Brown pork chops first and place in baking dish and pour sauce over them.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are done.

title: epps diner banana pudding
directions: Beat together the egg, sugar, flour, vanilla and food coloring. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
In an 8 x 12-inch dish, layer the vanilla wafers, bananas, pudding, vanilla wafers, bananas, pudding, etc.
Add meringue, if desired.

title: market salad
directions: In large bowl, combine first six ingredients; set aside.
In small bowl, combine vinegar, garlic powder and oregano.
Slowly add oil, whisking until smooth and thickened.
Add to vegetable and cheese mixture.
Toss gently.
Cover; chill thoroughly, stirring several times.

title: taco pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Spread in 10-inch pie plate.
Top with a layer of taco sauce, red onion, lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: texas trash
directions: I have
used other cereals, Crispix, for one, and eliminated others.
I used the Pepperidge Farm fish crackers instead of cheese
crackers.
I
think
you
will find you can't go far wrong.

title: party potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and cheese.
Then stir in potatoes.
Spread in ungreased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook ground beef and mix with taco seasoning.
Place meat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish and let cool.
Layer the other ingredients in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cornbread mix, eggs, milk and cottage cheese.
Add broccoli and onion.
Stir well. Pour melted margarine into mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture back into pan. Cook at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: slaw
directions: Heat to boil.
Cook 20 minutes.
Can approximately 10 pints.

title: applesauce doughnuts
directions: Fill heavy saucepan 2/3 full with vegetable oil; heat to 360° on deep fat frying thermometer.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and spices together; set aside.
Combine honey, brown sugar and eggs.
Add 2 tablespoons oil, beating thoroughly.
Alternately add dry ingredients and cider, mixing well.
Stir in applesauce and vanilla.
Carefully drop batter by level tablespoons, 3 or 4 at a time, into hot oil; do not overcrowd.
Fry, turning once, for 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove with tongs and drain on paper towel.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake white cake mix and let cool.
Mix pudding as directed; set aside.
Drain pineapple and set aside.
In punch bowl place 1/2 cup pudding.
Spread over bottom of bowl.
Crumble half of cake over pudding and spread 1/2 of remaining pudding over cake.
Add drained pineapple over pudding and add blueberry pie filling.
Spread to the edge so you can see the berries.
Add 1 bowl Cool Whip and crumble remaining cake.
Cover with pudding, pineapple, cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.
Top with 5 of the cherries.
You may use any fruit you like, even fresh fruit.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir the first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake on cookie sheet 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Pull from bone and layer in bottom of casserole dish. Top with chopped eggs. Mix together soup, celery, onions, almonds, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt. Pour and spread evenly over chicken and eggs. Top with chips. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add egg, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Gradually add the flour mixture. Beat until smooth.
Stir in the oatmeal; lightly flour hands and shape into 24 balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten with the bottom of a glass dipped in flour.
Insert a skewer or stick into each, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from the cookie sheet and allow to cool on wire racks. Decorate with frosting, coconut and candies to make faces.
Yields 24 (3-inch) cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli (use flowerets only).
Fry bacon and cool.
Mix dressing.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: jeannie's cranberry salad
directions: Boil water; add Jell-O and mix until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until mixed well.
Add oranges and pineapple; mix well.
Pour into Tupperware container, 7 1/2 to 8-cup capacity. Chill overnight.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: To sugar, flour and corn meal, add eggs, lemon juice, milk, butter and lemon rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cut with knife to check doneness.
Top should be golden brown feeling firm without being dry or hard.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add cream of chicken soup and blend into meat.
Then add onion soup mix, vegetables and water and mix well.
Pour into casserole baking dish.
Spread Tater Tots over top of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients: sugar, then cocoa, eggs, milk and vanilla. Mix well. Then add melted butter. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: turkey almond supreme
directions: You can use leftover turkey or roast a 2 pound turkey roast; cut turkey into bite size pieces.
Cook together butter, onion, celery and green pepper for 5 minutes.
Stir in turkey, soy sauce, water, pimento and mushroom soup.
Cook noodles and drain, stir sour cream into noodles and combine with the turkey mixture.
Put in a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the almonds over all.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; blend thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apples, apple juice concentrate, thickener and spice. Stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice, if desired, to keep apples lighter colored.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan and top with the second crust or pastry strips.
Seal the edges and cut slits in the top crust to allow the steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 55 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
May want to bake on cookie sheet.

title: earl biles party punch
directions: Mix jello and 1 cup water; set aside.
Mix lemonade with 2 cans water.
Set aside.
Mix orange juice with 1 1/2 cans water. After mixing individual ingredients, mix everything together.

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt with electric beater until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, about 1 teaspoon at a time, beating until smooth and glossy.
Continue beating and add Karo syrup, a little at a time, beating after each addition, until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
Makes enough to frost two 9-inch layers.

title: lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in hot water; let cool.
Then pour lye solution slowly into melted fat.
Stir until pretty cool.
Let this set overnight and cut into squares.

title: baked clams
directions: You will also need aluminum clam shells.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix oranges and bananas well.
Add walnuts.
Fold in yogurt. Add sugar to taste.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt and baking powder and set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and thoroughly combine.
Stir in nuts, dates, and cut up cherries. Portion dough using level measuring tablespoon.
Shape in balls. Roll in crushed corn flakes.
Garnish each cookie with a cherry piece (quartered cherries).
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 10-15 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: glazed apple wedges
directions: Core apples; cut into 1/2-inch thick wedges.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oleo, cook apples, brown sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and salt until apples are tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Spoon apples and their syrup into 6 dessert bowls.
If you like, serve with whipping cream.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Peel, core and slice apples in large saucepan.
Blend first 5 ingredients.
Stir in 10 cups water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Put apples in hot canning jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Use spatula to fill with hot syrup and help distribute syrup.
Adjust lid.
Process in boiling water.
Pints 15 minutes, quarts 20 minutes.
Makes 6 quarts. Store in cool place.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: crustless sausage-apple quiche
directions: Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well. Set aside.
Combine apples, spices, cheese and sausage.
Spoon into 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Combine eggs, half and half and biscuit mix.
Mix well.
Pour over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: mom's easy grape juice
directions: Place grapes and sugar in each quart jar.
Fill each jar to bottom of neck with hot tap water.
Wipe off the mouths of the jars and cover with hot lids and bands.
Process jar 20 minutes in a hot water bath.

title: snow frosting
directions: With electric mixer on medium speed, beat egg white with confectioners sugar and cream of tartar until mixture is thick and stiff peaks form when beater is slightly raised.
Use at once.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and nuts. Place in a large bowl. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Sift over fruit and stir to coat. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Add to fruit mixture and mix well by hand. Use just enough milk or juice to make a stiff batter. (Be careful not to use too much.) Drop by teaspoons onto lightly oiled cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in beet juice and vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Pour this hot solution over the beets and eggs.
Let stand overnight.
Then refrigerate.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix 2 sticks butter, flour and pecans.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: heather's reuben casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix together bread, water, eggs, corned beef, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Place half of the mixture in a large shallow casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray coating.
Spread evenly over bottom. Spread sauerkraut over mixture.
Spread dressing over the sauerkraut.
Spread with remaining corned beef mixture and sprinkle with Swiss cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and set. Serves 6 to 8.

title: batter fried cheese
directions: Fill containers halfway with milk, flour and bread crumbs. Add 3 eggs to milk.
Cut cheese into log strips.
Add cheese to milk and eggs.
(Do a couple at a time.)
Take out of milk and completely roll in flour.
Take out of flour and replace in milk mixture.
Take out of milk and place in Italian bread crumbs. Make sure it is completely covered.
When finished take out only what you are going to fry and refrigerate the rest for later.

title: alfredo
directions: Start the pasta first.
In 1/2 quart sauce pan, heat the butter, garlic and milk over a medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the butter melts and the milk is hot.
Do not boil.
Stir in the parmesan Cheese and pepper, continue heating until all is melted.
Pour sauce over the noodles, serve with additional parmesan and pepper as desired.

title: cranberry-pineapple jello mold
directions: Strain pineapple well.
Use juice and enough water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to boil, then add Jell-O.
Dissolve Jell-O and add whole cranberry sauce.
Cool.
Add pineapple and nuts. Pour into a 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate.

title: italian lemon cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually.
Add margarine.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk.
Add lemon extract.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to liquids.
Roll in a ball and refrigerate in Tupperware bowl.
Let sit one day before using. Pinch off dough and roll in hands to make biscuit.
Bake in greased pan 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Dough will keep 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain juice off green beans.
Mix green beans and soup together.
Put canned onion pieces on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour cream, and simmer all about 1 1/2 hours, until tender.
Before serving, add sour cream thickened with flour.
Heat and serve over rice.
Freezes well.

title: jiffy sandwich
directions: Place fried bacon on untoasted side of bread.
Mix grated cheese with Miracle Whip and place on top of bacon. Place under broiler until cheese is melted. Serve with sliced tomatoes on top.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and vanilla in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
When mixture comes to a boil, add pecans and cook until it reaches 234° or until soft ball when dropped in cold water. Add vanilla and beat until creamy. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: my mother's famous watermelon salad
directions: The day before the picnic, look at the melons; an even, balanced, level-sitting, ripe watermelon that fits ice chest or fridge; same for honeydew or Persian.
Place unchilled, washed, dried melons on drain-board; assemble utensils, clear bottom fridge shelf.
Place an oblong platter, French bread basket on top of watermelon; draw, dot with felt tip, a shallow cap around the top of watermelon.
With paring knife, cut along this cap line with knife parallel to board.
With 8-inch knife, remove cap with lever action, gently.
Cut off red melon into pieces bowl bite-sized. With scoop cut out large melon balls; put in 3 gallon bowl.
Smooth out inside of shell; cut up odd-sized pieces and juice into "pieces bowl".
Peel honeydews, Persians, tops to a "bowl"; repeat same process for melon balls and discard seeds.
Rinse, wipe off outside of shell and make a saw-toothed edge on watermelon shell; decorate, fill shell with a mix of all the kinds of melon balls, until shells are full.
Pour juice from the "pieces bowl" and "empties" into the watermelon.
Fill red shell until it is 1/2 full; wipe off, cover and chill.
Fill other shell with leftover melon balls and juice. Cover; chill.
The same for "pieces bowl".
Transport in ice chest, covered, on crushed ice.
Save Persian shell for breakfast.

title: cottage fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat baking sheet with Pam.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices and arrange in single layer on prepared baking sheet.
Sprinkle with generous amounts of paprika. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Turn potatoes over.
Sprinkle with more paprika.
Bake 12 more minutes or until lightly brown and fork-tender.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Roast peppers until skin peels off easily.
Make a small slit in sides of peppers.
Stuff with grated Swiss cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in the yolks.
Roll peppers in flour. Dip in eggs.
Fry until golden brown.

title: lima bean-apple casserole(14 minutes; a microwave oven recipe)
directions: In a microwave-safe 2-quart casserole, combine frozen beans, apple and water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) 8 to 10 minutes or until beans are tender, stirring twice.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in oleo until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in orange peel, orange juice and egg just until flour is moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together sugar and mayonnaise.
Mix salad and salad dressing all together.

title: sicilian veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on 18 x 12-inch cookie sheet.
Cook at 425° until lightly brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on top of cooked dough.
Chop vegetables into small pieces.
Layer in order given.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 quart berries and combine with water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add butter and food coloring.

title: nell's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone.
Put in bottom of pan.
Mix broth with soup and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and butter.
Drop or pour over chicken.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Brown last part of cooking.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream
the oleo until fluffy.
Combine egg and vanilla. Stir well
into	oleo.
Combine dry ingredients and gradually add to first
mixture.
Preheat
oven
to	300°. Spray cookie sheets with
nonstick vegetable spray.
Place a tablespoon of dough several
inches
apart
on	cookie	sheet.	Bake
for 15 minutes. Remove
immediately
from
pan (they harden and will break apart). Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chocolate granny
directions: Combine graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter. Press firmly into bottom of 19 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Using 3 1/2 cups milk, prepare pudding as directed.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding.
Garnish with grated chocolate or chopped nuts.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and bring to a boil over low flame. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate 2 or 3 days.

title: cheddar cheese quiche
directions: Bake pie crust for 10 minutes.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Beat all 4 eggs.
Saute onion and frozen broccoli.
Mix all ingredients into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain water off.
Put potatoes in glass rectangular pan.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the cocoa, sugar, milk and margarine; let boil for 1 minute.
Take from heat.
Mix the peanut butter, Quick oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: french country chicken
directions: In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine vegetables and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Arrange chicken breasts on vegetables.
In small bowl, combine other ingredients (except remaining onions). Pour over chicken and vegetables.

Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until chicken is done. Baste chicken with wine sauce and top with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and shrimp chowder
directions: In medium saucepan combine milk, garlic powder, thyme and broccoli.
Cook over medium heat until hot, stirring occasionally. Gently stir in tomato and shrimp; cook until shrimp is opaque. Makes about 3 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and butter flavored Crisco in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil; stir constantly. Continue to boil for 7 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate until it is melted.
Add the remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add shrimp and seasonings.
Cook until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Add eggs, stirring until well mixed with other ingredients.
Add rice and cook until a golden color.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve at once.
Cooking time:
15 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: terri's chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Line 4 cookie sheets with wax paper. In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, mix butter, cocoa, sugar and milk. Keep mixing and stirring until the mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add the vanilla and peanut butter. Stir until the peanut butter melts. Add the oatmeal and stir. Drop by teaspoons onto the wax paper. Chill in the refrigerator. Enjoy!

title: best chocolate pie
directions: In pot, combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Stir and get out lumps.
Add milk and cook over low heat.
Stir as it thickens. When mixture gets very hot, add beaten egg yolks slowly as you stir.
Continue cooking and stirring until very thick.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Beat egg whites to make meringue.
(If using sugar, use only one tablespoon for each egg white.)

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature.
Mix cheeses, butter and garlic powder with electric mixer.
Chill about 3 hours.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.
Use as a spread for crackers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil until blended. Remove and pour over any meat.
Refrigerate.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples and spoon into pastry lined pie pan.
Then combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour; add 1/2 cup margarine (soft) until it looks like crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Put pie in grocery bag; fold end twice and fasten with clips.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: ragout raleigh
directions: In a very heavy skillet, arrange half strips bacon over the bottom. Cut the round steak in strips and cover the bacon with the strips. Add salt and pepper. Cover the meat with the sliced carrots and onions; top with the potatoes.

Add salt, pepper and parsley flakes. Cover and cook over very low heat for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until done. Do not lift the lid unless it is cooking too fast and needs a little water. It can be cooked longer if necessary, just make sure it is on low heat.

title: scalloped potatoes with chicken
directions: In a medium saucepan, simmer potato slices in chicken broth, covered, with extra salt if desired, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Meanwhile, in medium size skillet or another saucepan, melt margarine and saute onion and celery until barely tender.
Add flour; stir until blended.
Let cook a moment or two to eliminate starchy taste.
Have oven preheating to 350°. Gradually whisk in the chicken broth (drain from potatoes directly into the skillet), stirring constantly.
Add thyme, basil and pepper; simmer for about 3 minutes.
Whisk in the Parmesan cheese. Place 1/2 the chicken pieces in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add 1/2 the potato slices and 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat layers; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350°oven for 30 minutes.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Pound veal thoroughly on both sides; dredge in flour and brown in butter and olive oil.
Remove veal from pan.
Place in ovenproof dish and set in warm oven (250°).

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Roll chicken in seasoned flour as for frying.
Place in large baking dish with chicken around the sides of dish.
Place instant rice in center of dish, put onion soup over rice.
Pour boiling water over rice and soup until covered.
Pour mushroom soup over chicken.
Allow to bake in moderate oven until chicken is tender and brown on top, approximately 90 minutes.

title: chilli
directions: Cook meat until brown (drain fat).
Mix in seasonings; add rest of ingredients.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits, cut each slice in fourths.
Place in plastic bag, add sugar and cinnamon; shake.
Place the biscuits in Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and pour over biscuits in Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, combine ground beef, tomato paste, juice, water, chili powder, salt, pepper, sugar, oregano, tomato sauce and garlic.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes longer or until spaghetti is tender.
Stir frequently.
Add onion rings last 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: smith island pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, salt and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add flour alternately with milk and water mixed together, blending well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into a large greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Turn oven temperature to 325 degrees. Bake for about 2 hours.

title: peach preserves
directions: Grind or chop the peaches, oranges, lemons and maraschino cherries.
Add sugar and let stand for 1 hour.
Cook 4 cups at a time for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy; add eggs and vanilla; sift flour, baking powder and salt into creamed mixture. Blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: green beans with cheese and peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart oval casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine green beans, red pepper strips, salt and pepper in prepared dish.
Place cream cheese and milk in small saucepan; heat over low heat, stirring until melted.
Add blue cheese; stir only until combined.
Pour cheese mixture over green bean mixture and stir until green beans are coated.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine in small bowl; sprinkle evenly over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut crust off French bread and dice into 1-inch cubes.
Add 1 diced onion and hard-boiled eggs (cut up).
Mix. Let stand overnight, then add shrimp, crab meat and mayo.
Let stand for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: apple cinnamon pound cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mixture will be a heavy dough. Pour into a floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
When done, leave in pan, pour buttermilk sauce over cake and let cool completely.

title: joan's mostaccioli
directions: In large, heavy stock pan, heat oil and brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil slowly.
Simmer for at least 1 1/2 hours.
It's much better the day after and freezes well.
Keeps in the fridge for at least one week.
Cook mostaccioli as directed on the box.

title: surprise cherry squares
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour, beating well.
Then stir in flavorings.
Pour the batter into a slightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, spreading evenly.
Lightly cut through batter with a small knife to mark off 24 squares.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon pie filling in the center of each square.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Batter will puff up around filling while baking.
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes. Cut into squares.
Remove from pan or leave in pan.
Drizzle while warm with 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 to 2 tablespoons of milk, mixed well.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: arizona chalupa dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Spread bean dip in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with avocado mixture then top with sour cream mixture. Sprinkle in layers with onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese. Broil until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips (large round ones).

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add milks, water and fruit.
Place in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: sausage ring
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press lightly into greased 6-cup ring mold.
Loosen edges with spatula and unmold into shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, drain fat and move to warm platter.

title: easy homemade apple butter
directions: Put in crock-pot on low, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.
Cook at least 8 hours or more if possible.
When it begins to stick to spoon and has turned brown, put in hot Mason jars while hot and seal with clean lids.
Cool completely, then refrigerate.
Makes great gifts!

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Trim all fat from chicken; cut into strips (6 1/2-inch strips).
Marinate in the white wine, soy sauce, lemon or lime juice and garlic powder for 1 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally. Slice onion and pepper; saute or stir-fry until tender-crisp in heavy skillet coated with Pam.
Remove to bowl and keep warm. Cook mushrooms in same pan for 1 minute.
Put in bowl with pepper and onion.
Saute chicken in same pan until lightly browned.
Warm tortillas as directed on package; fill each tortilla with chicken and vegetables.
Add cheese and/or salsa.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix ingredients like pie crust.
Add enough milk to make medium dough.
Shape into large biscuits with hands.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: deviled ham and tuna
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Chill.
May be used as salad, on a sandwich or to stuff a tomato.

title: sweet cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix ingredients until dough forms (may appear dry).
Turn dough out onto a bread board dusted with baking mix and gently roll the dough in baking mix to coat.
Knead dough 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter dipped in baking mix.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: hamburger bean hot dish
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Brown hamburger and diced onion.
Add the rest of ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cassoulet
directions: Soak beans overnight, then drain.
Put beans, water, broth and all spices, onion and garlic in pot.
Simmer 1 hour, then add pork chops and chicken; cook until done.
Add sausage about 30 minutes before done.
Long, slow cooking brings a better flavor.

title: sour cream cutout cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, vanilla, eggs and sour cream. Add the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Chill. Roll and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
In a saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar and the cornstarch.
Stir in the pineapple liquid.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining sugar and pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with the pineapple mixture.
Top with second crust, crimp and bake at 375°
for 50 to 60 minutes until crust is golden.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 2-quart microwave dish.
Place apple slices in dish.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake for 16 minutes, turning 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.

title: chili picasso
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.
Serve as a dip with Frito-Lay corn chips.
Keep in refrigerator and add tomatoes and peppers often and other seasonings as needed.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Melt butter in baking pan and put biscuits in hot pan.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: mary's fruit cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well.
Add liquids alternately with dry ingredients (except 1 cup flour).
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in fruits and nuts that have been dredged in one cup flour.
Steam 3 hours and dry out in slow oven for 1 hour.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Place spices in cheesecloth.
Bring liquid to boiling point. Simmer together for 20 minutes.
Remove bag and store, covered, for reuse.
Taste and simmer longer if desired. Serve with cinnamon stick in front of a roaring fire!

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes. Let cool, then peel.
Then dice potatoes.
Cook eggs and peel, then dice eggs.
Chop onion.
Mix potatoes, onion and eggs together.
Mix Miracle Whip, milk, vinegar, sugar, mustard and garlic powder together, then pour over the mixture. Chill and serve.
To make smaller batch, just half everything.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook 45 minutes at 350°, covered.
Uncover, add cheese and melt.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; stand aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; lay on paper towel to cool.
Break cauliflower and broccoli in bite-size pieces into salad bowl; add diced onion, shredded carrot and shredded cheese. Crumble bacon over top.
Pour mayonnaise dressing over top; toss and refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix or toss before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add egg; blend well.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, cinnamon and baking soda; mix well.
Fold in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes or until light golden brown.
Store in loosely covered container.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: In 9 x 12-inch pan, slice Twinkies in half to make layer in bottom of pan.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Spread over Twinkies after thickened.
Top with Cool Whip.
I use chocolate pudding.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss ingredients all together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat and boil the first 3 ingredients until it forms a soft ball.
Add peanut butter.
Set in sink in cold water and stir until it becomes thick.

title: peanut butter chew
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter and peanut butter; stir in sugar, vanilla and eggs until blended well.
Add flour and stir until combined.
Do not beat.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: quick macaroni supper
directions: Brown meat slightly and add vegetables.
Add tomato sauce or a quart of tomatoes and a small can tomato paste for color.
Set aside.
Boil 2 cups macaroni in salted water.
Mix all together and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: glazed julienne carrots, turnips and rutabaga
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes until the vegetables are crisp-tender and all liquid is evaporated.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Combine shortening, salt and vanilla and add 1/4 of the sugar. Add milk and remaining sugar alternately.
Mix until smooth and of spreading consistency.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and milk. Add Bisquick and vanilla. Form in small balls and roll in sugar. Flatten with fork.
Cook about 6 minutes at 375°.

title: sugar jumbles
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda and add to first mixture.
Beat 2 minutes. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cookies should be soft.
Cool slightly, then remove from cookie sheet.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar for 15-20 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, lemon extract,
Then fold in the 7-UP drink. Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: raw broccoli and fantastic dip
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli with 1 1/2 stem.
Split the large one to make bite-sized.
Combine vinegar, oil, garlic, sugar and dill for marinade in jar.
Shake.
Put broccoli in medium-size baggie and pour marinade over.
Tie and refrigerate up to one day before serving.
Mix mayo, curry, catsup, Worcestershire sauce together for dip.
Refrigerate.
Drain broccoli and serve with dip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl stir first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour into crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
(Do not overbake).

title: fresh peach crisp
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Set aside. Combine peaches, extract and water.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch square dish.
Sprinkle flour mixture over peaches, then sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Beat until light. Mix soda in buttermilk. Add bananas and part of flour; beat well. Add the soda-milk mixture; stir in rest of flour. Beat real well. Makes 3 loaves. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pig in the blanket
directions: If you use sliced cheese, fold in four pieces and I use 2 per pig in the blanket.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate or 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange broccoli and chicken.
In small bowl, combine soup and milk; pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
In a cup combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water; set aside.
In large bowl, mix 2 3/4 cups warm water, sugar, salt and shortening. Gradually add 5 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add yeast and rest of flour until dough is workable.
Put on floured board, knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover with hot towel.
Let rise until double in size.
Put into greased loaf pan.
Let rise.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan, brush with butter.
Cool on wire rack.

title: southern b b q
directions: 1. Put pork roast, 1 c. water, cloves, and 1 large onion (sliced) in crock pot. Cook overnight on very low heat.
2. Take pork out next morning and let cool. Discard juices
saving 1/2 c.
After pork has cooled pull it apart
using two forks (or your fingers). Throw away any fat.
3. Put shredded pork back in crock pot. Add diced onion
and BBQ sauce. Cook on low heat another 5-6 hours. Add
reserved juice if needed.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in the sugar, then the oil. Combine all dry ingredients.
Add to the first mixture alternately with the zucchini.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Scald scallops; pour boiling water over them and let stand 10 minutes.
Saute celery, onions and mushrooms in butter or margarine.
Using 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons flour make gravy in pan. Add 1 to 1 1/2 cups water.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in large casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to shortening mixture alternating with milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.

title: crunchy date rounds
directions: Form into balls; roll in sugared cereal flakes (crushed). Press a nut into top of cookie or may omit dates and add chocolate chips and place chocolate wafer on top.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry crunch dessert
directions: You will need an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: beef for buns
directions: Cut roast in pieces.
Put in a crock-pot (low).
Add other ingredients.
Cook 8 to 10 hours or until very tender.
Pull meat off in small pieces.
Put back in roasting juices and serve over buns.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix sugar cocoa, and butter.
Beat in eggs and add vanilla. Mix well, then stir in flour and nuts.
Beat one minute.
Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
While warm spread marshmallow cream evenly over cake; cool before icing.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine onions, oil and garlic in a large heavy pot.
Cover and braise slowly for 40 to 45 minutes.
After 30 minutes, remove the cover.
Season with salt and pepper and cook, uncovered, until tender and golden.
Stir from time to time; do not brown.
Lift onions into pie shell with a slotted spoon to remove excess moisture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and decorate with anchovy fillets and black olives.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Chop up celery, bell pepper and onion; saute.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: crunchy peanut butter cups
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, peanut butter, vanilla and butter. Knead with hands until blended. Add Beer Nuts* and knead until mixture is smooth. Spread peanut butter mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Smooth and flatten surface of mixture by placing sheet of waxed paper on top and "roll" over surface with a small juice glass or rolling pan. Break chocolate bar into several pieces and melt over double boiler; spread melted chocolate evenly over peanut butter mixture. Refrigerate until chocolate has hardened, about 15 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: In large kettle, cook bacon until almost crisp. Add green pepper, onion and garlic. Cook until tender. Add beef cubes and brown on all sides. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper. Add sugar. Stir and cook for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and broth. Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender. One half hour before serving, add potatoes. Cook until tender. Garnish each serving with a dollop of sour cream. Serves 8.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Separate whites and place in egg tray. Place yellow in bowl. Beat in squirt of pickle juice and salt and pepper. Scoop by spoon into egg whites and serve.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak dried chopped apricots in water at least 1 hour.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup liquid.
Cream margarine and sugar; add egg. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and reserved water.
Stir in apricots and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan or 2 small pans at 350° about 1 hour.
Let cool before slicing.
This freezes well.
If not enough water leftover from apricots, add water to get desired amount.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: First Layer:
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Mix in pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: lemon fluff cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add lemon rind.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites and blend in well.
Bake in 2 greased pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hash browned potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes with flour, onion, cream, salt and pepper. Heat butter in heavy skillet.
Add potatoes.
Pack firmly to make an even layer and brown.
Reduce heat and cook for 20 minutes. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese during last 5 minutes of cooking. Fold over like an omelette onto serving dish and serve immediately.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and stir till dissolved.
Add lemon juice, cold water and pineapple juice.
Stir well.

title: carrot cake
directions: Measure all dry ingredients in sifter.
Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and oil in small amounts at a time, stirring well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into three greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done when tested with a toothpick or cake tester.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice with water.
Mix all ingredients, except Velveeta, in a large bowl.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with the slices of Velveeta.
Bake at 400° until cheese starts to brown.

title: chicken in mustard sauce
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chicken.
Brown in margarine until golden.
Mix sauce ingredients, mayonnaise and Grey Poupon; add zucchini, squash, onion, and garlic to sauce.
Place chicken and pan drippings in the bottom of a casserole.
Pour sauce/vegetable mixture on top of chicken and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven for approximately 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Enjoy.

title: best-ever cookies
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, oil, egg and vanilla in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar; add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Stir in cereal, coconut, oatmeal and nuts.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart; flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Top with sauerkraut.
Put slice of cheese on top of sauerkraut.
Pour Thousand Island dressing over top.
Bake at 300°, covered, for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Uncover for last 10 minutes.

title: spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook spinach according to package.
Squeeze out all liquid. Mix all ingredients and chill 2 hours.
Roll into 75 one inch balls.
Freeze or refrigerate until ready to cook.
Cook in 300° oven for 30 minutes on ungreased sheet.

title: apple fritters
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; mix well.
Stir flour and baking powder together; add to apple mixture and stir well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into deep oil heated to 375°.
Fry fritters until golden (about 3 minutes).
Drain on paper towels. Dust with powdered sugar.
Serve hot.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all together with electric mixer. Pour into greased pie pan. Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 300°. Use Cool Whip or ice cream on top.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix with mayonnaise, sour cream, bacon bits, green onions and dressing mix.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Spread mixture on 8 to 10 flour tortillas.
Roll up and slice. Best if refrigerated 24 hours before serving.
Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Add remaining sauce ingredients.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently, until thickened, approximately 1/2 hour. Cook spaghetti.
Serve 4-ounce ladle of sauce over 4 ounces spaghetti.
Serves 50 (4 ounces sauce and 4 ounces spaghetti per serving).

title: linguine primavera
directions: In skillet, over medium heat, cook and stir broccoli, carrots, onion, Italian seasoning, garlic and pepper in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add tomato. Cook for 1 minute or until vegetables are tender-crisp. Toss with hot linguine, Egg Beaters and cheese. Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: republican dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts like a pastry.
Press in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex until flat (mold up sides).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until light and creamy.
Fold in 1 large Cool Whip.
Spread on cool crust.
Then mix chocolate pudding and milk and place on cream cheese layer.
Spread small Cool Whip on top.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: lemon-fried chicken
directions: Cut fryer in quarters.
Combine lemon juice, oil and seasoning to make marinade.
Pour over chicken. Be sure all chicken parts are in contact with marinade.
Marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator. Drain chicken. Dust with flour. Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Place chicken in hot oil and fry until golden brown on all sides.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday magic salad
directions: Completely dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Stir in eggnog, Cool Whip and strawberries until mixed well.
Chill until firm.

title: sugar-free strawberry jam
directions: In a saucepan, bring soda to a boil.
Remove from the heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Stir in strawberries and lemon juice.
Pour into jars or containers; cover and refrigerate up to 3 weeks.
Do not freeze.

title: scones
directions: Lightly grease a baking sheet and preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, sugar, and salt into a bowl.
Grate butter into the flour mixture, mixing through gently; use your fingers to rub together any lumps.
Add the milk and mix together until a sticky dough has formed.
Put the dough mixture onto a lightly floured surface and knead with your fingers until smooth.
Press or roll the dough flat (about 2cm thick).
Cut out scone circles with the cutter until no dough remains.
Place all scones on the baking sheet (they should not touch each other) and bake on the center rack for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook together, stirring constantly until bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add sweet milk, vanilla and powdered sugar; beat until spreadable.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liners.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs until smooth.
Fill cups and add toppings.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp a la creole
directions: Use small fish such as catfish, lemonfish or shark.
If you use a fish with scales, you will have to remove the scales.
The fish must be gutted and you can remove the head and fins if you prefer, but the tail and fins get wonderfully crunchy and delicious by deep frying.
Some preparations call for both a drench and a dredge; some call for neither and some for just a dredge.
Fry until golden brown and crispy on the outside.
When you eat whole fish be particularly careful of bones.

title: rainbow punch
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water; set aside.
In large punch bowl, combine pineapple juice, real lemon juice and gelatin mixture.
Chill.
Just before serving, add sherbet and club soda.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: green beans and mushrooms in sauce
directions: Cook beans; drain.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Saute onions.
Add mushrooms and lemon juice.
Stir constantly.
Combine paprika, 2 tablespoons flour and salt.
Sprinkle over mushrooms. Cook 1 minute.
Add pepper sauce and cream.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Add beans and blend well.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalk.
Wash thoroughly and cut into spears.
Cook broccoli, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Arrange in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Combine soups and next 4 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Based on 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
While macaroni is cooking, brown ground chuck and onion with salt and pepper.
Drain.
When done, mix macaroni and
ground
chuck
mixture
together
and add pizza sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce and sugar.
Mix all together and add several dashes of garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix in the order listed.
Dough is very stiff.
Drop by spoonfuls; press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: maggie's beet top soup
directions: Combine everything except milk in large kettle.
Simmer slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until vegetables are tender.
When done, add 1 can evaporated milk.
Add extra water if needed.
Beat tops, green onions and dill.
May be frozen when in season for winter use.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato and cucumber.
Arrange tuna mixture, tomato and cucumber on serving plates.
Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday soup
directions: Cook turkey carcass, skin and etc. and skim the fat off the broth.
Place in large kettle and add all the vegetables and rice. Simmer until vegetables are cooked and flavors blended.
You can add additional bouillon and salt and pepper to taste.
A very good way to use up leftover turkey and very good at the holiday season.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Cool cake.
Whip cream with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Frost bottom cake layer with whipped cream.
Slice banana over cream. Cover banana with more whipped cream.
Add top layer and repeat. Frost sides of cake with remaining whipped cream.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered container.
(Covering the sliced bananas with the whipping cream will help prevent darkening.)

title: baked chicken
directions: Bake in uncovered casserole dish for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in preheated 300° oven.

title: onion lover casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until brown.
Drain fat.
Add onions and pepper.
Cook and stir onions until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: greek hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and cut lengthwise into quarters.
Arrange potatoes on platter, sprinkle with salt and pepper, olive oil, vinegar, scallions and oregano.
Garnish with parsley and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: yummy jello salad
directions: Mix raspberry jello and water together until dissolved.
Add raspberries.
Let set slightly.
Add crushed pineapple with juice. Refrigerate until set.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O,
cup water and pineapple in a pan; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Let mixture cool completely.
Pour mixture into large mixing bowl.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and
nuts; beat
until
smooth.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pineapple ham glaze
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together in a small pan.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Continue stirring and cook 1 minute.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: oven stew
directions: Use heavy roaster or Dutch oven with tight-fitting lid.
Layer ingredients as listed.
Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 250° for 6 to 7 hours.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together (using hands to mix is quickest and easiest). Shape into round loaf and place in crock. Spread extra catsup over top of meat loaf. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 4 to 6 hours). Freezes well for once-a-month cooking plan; freeze before cooking.

title: honey mustard marinade (for grilling)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush on chicken while grilling. (Best to marinate chicken or pork for about 8 hours before grilling.)

title: lipton stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove core from cabbage, then remove the 20 largest leaves.
Bring water to boil in large saucepan; add cabbage leaves and cook for 3 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: bean taco layered dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Spread over bean dip layer.
Mash avocado with lemon juice.
Spread over mayonnaise and sour cream layer.
Sprinkle cheese, onion and tomato on top.
Garnish with tortilla chips.

title: pecan pie filling
directions: Cream butter; gradually add firmly packed brown sugar and cream well.
Blend in light corn syrup and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, slightly beaten, and chopped pecans.
Turn into pastry lined pan and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, salt and nutmeg together.
Add eggs and ice water and then flour.
Roll on a floured board and cut into shapes.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 - 15 minutes or until brown around edges.
While still warm, remove from baking sheet and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan, spread 2 cans refried beans.
In mixing bowl, combine sour cream and taco mix, then spread mixture over beans.
Top with layer of chopped green onions.
Sprinkle on chopped black olives, guacamole (commercially prepared dip is fine) and diced tomato.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Allow flavors to blend 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ruth's hot potato salad
directions: Brown bacon until done; remove from drippings.
Also, remove some of the fat.
Add onions and simmer until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add vinegar, sugar, water, salt and celery seed.
Cook until thickened.
Fold in bacon, potatoes, eggs and parsley.
Heat until it is hot.
Serves 6.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Drain beans, peas, corn and pimento.
Combine all ingredients.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add canned milk, sweet milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour into freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: crab and cream cheese dip
directions: Blend well.
Top with slivered almonds.
Bake in ovenproof dish at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: calzones
directions: Thaw the bread dough.
Divide each loaf into 5 parts each. Roll each piece on a floured board or stretch with your hands, making 10 (7-inch) squares.
Fold your favorite fillings into square; form a turnover.
Pinch edges to seal.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Heat sauce and use as a topping.
Freeze unbaked Calzones to use another day.
Thaw and bake as directed.
Makes 10 servings.

title: celery stuffing
directions: Simmer celery in water for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Cook onion in butter; do not brown. Combine seasonings and croutons.
Add celery, 1 cup celery liquid and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Stuff body cavity of turkey or chicken.
Cook turkey at 25 minutes per pound at 325°.
Stuffing will fill a 10 to 14 pound turkey.

title: "almost home-made" crisp and sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles thoroughly and discard liquid.
Thinly slice across pickles.
Drain in colander for 4 - 5 hours.
Fill a 6 gallon jar about 1/4 full of pickles, sugar, garlic and hot sauce.
Alternate ingredients until all pickles are packed in jar.
Tighten lid.
Let stand at room temperature 5 days, turning jar once or twice a day. Refrigerate.

title: skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Simmer onion and green pepper in a little water in skillet. Add beef and brown.
Add macaroni, tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, until macaroni is cooked to suit your taste, adding more water as needed to keep from sticking and getting too dry.
Serves 6.

title: gold angel food cake
directions: Beat yolks good; add water and beat again.
Gradually add sugar, then vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt 4 times and gradually add to mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff with cream of tartar and fold into mixture.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 300° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: marilyn's summer squash casserole
directions: Cook and slice squash and onions in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrot. Combine with squash and onions, folding gently.
Reserve 1/4 cup croutons.
Combine remaining with melted margarine and place in greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup croutons over vegetable mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: cheese pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sour cream.
Add sugar. Mix some more.
Add milk and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker pie shell.

title: doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until set.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields about 4 dozen cookies.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk to a
boil;
add
rice and sugar.
Cook over low heat until done, 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally. While that is
cooking,
in another bowl, beat egg yolks, beat egg whites and
set
aside.
Remove
rice
mixture
from stove; add egg yolks and vanilla.
Return to low heat until it bubbles and thickens.
