Fold
in
egg
whites;
cook
until egg whites are all folded in.
Transfer to another bowl.

title: cajun mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems from caps. Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, pepper, salt and Tabasco sauce. Increase heat to medium high. Cover and cook, stirring frequently, for around 20 minutes.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix all together and bake as needed.
Rest will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Can be frozen.
Bake about 20 minutes at 375°.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook in casserole for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.

title: favorite bran bread
directions: Cream margarine or butter and sugar well, add molasses and buttermilk.
Beat eggs and add to first mixture.
Next, add the All-Bran.
Then add flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt (sifted together).
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour or more in 350° oven until done.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Mix each jello separately, using less water than package directs, and put in 8 x 8-inch pan each color.
When set, cut in 1/2-inch cubes.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes, then add 1/2 cup hot water.
Add pineapple juice; let set until soupy.
Whip the cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add pineapple.
Add to gelatin mixture, then add cubed jellos.
Save a few for garnish.

title: beef marinade
directions: Whisk the soy sauce, sesame oil, vinegar and a generous amount of pepper in a medium bowl.
Mix in the garlic.
Pour over your favorite beef (flank steaks, chuck roast, etc.), turning to coat all sides.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight, turning the steaks occasionally.
Now the beef is ready for your grill or broiler.

title: crazy baked beans
directions: Cook onion and apple in small amount of boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, garlic and celery seed in butter.
Add mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
In greased baking dish, layer spaghetti, chicken sauce and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
This makes a large amount.

title: yummy jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: pig-licking cake
directions: Mix cake mix by directions on the box. Add the small box of pudding mix and blend. Fold in the mandarin oranges and bake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, cream margarine.
Cut heat to medium; stir 7 minutes.
Turn off heat and add marshmallows, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 13 x 15-inch pan. Let get cold and cut into small squares.

title: african froth
directions: Combine in blender the first 4 ingredients.
Add apricots, dates or fresh strawberries.
Blend until smooth, adding honey or a touch of sugar for taste.
Pour into two 8 ounce glasses and serve with shredded coconut sprinkled over the top.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Mix until soft dough forms.
Lightly grease cookie sheet. Smooth dough into a ball and knead 20 times on a lightly floured surface.
Pat dough on bottom and sides of pan.

title: cream cheese cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: citrus pineapple mold
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges. Keep juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Set aside.

title: boudin dip
directions: With mixer, whip the cream cheese until smooth. Add sour cream. Take boudin out of casing and add to cheese mixture with spoon or spatula until well blended. Serve with Sociables crackers or large dip Fritos.

title: brown rice and vegetable paella
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, heat the oil over medium heat.
Add the onion, red pepper and garlic and cook, stirring often, until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add the brown rice and cook, stirring, until the rice turns opaque, about 2 minutes.
Stir in the vegetable bouillon, tomato juice, salt and cayenne and bring to a boil.
Transfer to a 2-quart baking dish. Stir in the artichoke hearts.
Cover tightly and bake until the liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in the chickpeas, peas or broccoli and olives.
Cover and bake, just until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Garnish the paella with the lemon wedges so each guest can squeeze on lemon juice to taste. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, egg, milk, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Shape into 12 meatballs.
Brown in hot oil in skillet. Remove excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour mixture over meatballs. Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes. Turn often until meatballs are well glazed.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or noodles!

title: broccoli rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together (mixes easily).
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° until slightly brown or heated through (about 20 minutes).

title: crunchy sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions and set aside. Cook sausage, ground beef and onion over medium heat, stirring to crumble.
Drain off drippings.
Add rice, mushrooms, water chestnuts and soy sauce.
Stir well.
Spoon into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove and allow to set at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Dump all together and
mix
well.
Put	into
a covered bowl. For each cup hot cocoa,
put 1/3 cup of this mixture in cup.
Fill with water and heat in microwave.

title: sausage strata(a chappell christmas morning tradition)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim crusts from bread.
Fit bread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage; drain.
Stir in mustard.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half cream, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour this mixture over bread, meat and cheese in pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May be made a day ahead.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Cook same as above with foil on.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and concentrate until smooth.
Fold in marshmallow creme.
Serve with fruit.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields:
2 cups.

title: cabbage lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain well. Add sauce.
In a large casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, layer meat, cabbage and cheese.
Continue to layer until all ingredients are used.
Cover and bake at 350° until cabbage is tender, about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brown rice
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour rice in dish.
Slice butter and put on top of rice.
Dump onion soup and consome soup (do not stir).
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix cool whip with cream cheese slowly and add in pistachio pudding.
Then add pineapple, fruit cocktail, and marshmallows. Chill and serve.

title: spanish rice
directions: In skillet saute green pepper, onion and garlic in olive oil until tender.
Stir in herbs, rice, chopped tomatoes, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil over moderately high heat. Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 22 g, protein .5 g, fat 5 g, calories 134.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Make the pudding as directed.
Drain pineapple and add to the pudding.
Add Cool Whip after pudding has chilled.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill overnight.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Place 1/3 of noodles in casserole. Add 1/3 can of tuna and 1/3 can soup.
Repeat layers twice more.
Cover with milk and bake until done (about 1 hour) at 350°.

title: butterscotch morsels(kids recipe)
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot (not boiling) water in double boiler or in microwave.
Add noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bread stick snacks
directions: Split bacon slices in half lengthwise, enough for number of bread sticks desired.
Roll bread sticks in cheese in a shallow dish or plate.
Wrap bacon slices around sticks in a spiral fashion.
Roll in cheese again.
Bake in moderate oven, on rack over baking sheet or pan, for about 15 minutes, or until bacon is crisp.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over chopped vegetables, stirring well.
Keeps well in refrigerator for about 3 weeks.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of pie plate.
Cover cream cheese with chili, then pour salsa over chili and top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sausage biscuit bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large saucepan, heat together sausage and shredded cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Stir in Bisquick until smooth.
Cool.
Chill for 30 minutes for ease in handling.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove.
Place on paper towels to drain.
Serve warm.
(Freezes well after baking; reheat in slow oven.)

title: spicy pork strips
directions: Slice pork into 1/4-inch thick strips. Thread onto bamboo skewers. Put in shallow pan. Blend all ingredients in saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves. Pour over skewers for 30 minutes. Broil 3 minutes on each side.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat and onion until light in color. Add milk, soup and chiles.
Mix well and then pour over Doritos in an electric skillet and top with cheese.
Put lid on skillet and heat at medium until mixture bubbles and cheese is melted.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix all and place into a double boiler; add 1 quart more water.
Cook until thick.
Use more water if necessary.
Beat mixture with an egg beater.
You may want to add a teaspoon to glycerin to make it more pliable and 1 cup talcum to give it a pleasant smell and better texture.
Separate mixture and mix in powdered paint for colors.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually cream in sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add extracts to milk; mix well.
Add flour alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Place batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven at 325°.
Bake for 60 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini-carrot bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, egg and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover tightly with waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Refrigerate dough at least 2 hours.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for 3 days.
To use, cut off amount needed and shape as desired.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir meat and onions in skillet until meat is brown and onions are tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, green pepper, 2 tablespoons flour, the basil and oregano. Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk, oil, 1 cup flour and salt until smooth.
Pour over cheese.
Bake until puffy and golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Wash strawberries; cut in small pieces if they are large. Spread in shells.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add water and cook over low heat until it thickens, stirring occasionally.
Set aside just to cool briefly.
Add jello to this mixture.
Pour over strawberries evenly.
Chill.
Serve with whip cream or ice cream.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer in heavy bottomed saucepan for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Will keep two weeks under refrigeration.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss. Serve in chilled bowl or mound salad in lettuce cups and garnish with cherries.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Pour the sugar into the rhubarb; let stand at least 10 to 12 hours.
Pour rhubarb mix and berry pie filling into large pan; bring to boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Fill containers, leaving 1/4 to 1/2 inch for expansion and freeze.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into greased dish. Chill. Cut into bars.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar thoroughly. Gradually add white sugar and continue creaming. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Combine baking powder, salt and flour. Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.

Add vanilla and nuts. Blend well. Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done. Cool cake for 15 minutes before removing from pan. Dust with powdered sugar before serving, if desired.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Combine meat with soup mix.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Mix in green peppers.
Make mashed potatoes and mix in sour cream and butter.
Layer on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix. Spread on a 12-inch round serving platter. Blend avocados, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth. Spread on top of bean mixture. Top with shredded lettuce, cheese, taco sauce and olive slices. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: never fail meringue for pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thick and clear.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until it mounds; gradually add sugar and add cooked cooled cornstarch mixture until meringue stands in stiff peaks. Place over pie and bake as directed.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Place in casserole dish with chicken.
Add soup, sauteed onions, chilies, tomatoes and cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: perky potatoes supreme
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl all ingredients except chips. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy cabbage casserole
directions: Put salt, onion and cabbage in water.
Boil just enough to wilt cabbage.
Drain and place
half
of
hot
cabbage in a generously buttered baking dish.
Cover
with
a
layer of 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Then
top
with
cup
cracker crumbs. Repeat all 3 layers,
ending
with
cracker
crumbs.
Dot with margarine and carefully pour in milk to cover crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 to 30
minutes or until casserole is bubbling and light brown.

title: cornmeal pan cakes
directions: You can omit the cornmeal and use 1 cup flour instead, for regular pan cakes.

title: cornflake-fried chicken breasts
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs with milk, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Add chicken pieces; refrigerate 1 hour.
In a plastic or paper bag, combine crushed cornflakes and biscuit mix.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time; shake to coat well.
Place on a baking sheet and refrigerate chicken for 2 hours.
Heat 1 1/2 to 2 inches of oil in a large saucepan or deep-fat fryer to 375°.
Fry chicken in batches without crowding, turning, 5 minutes a side, until browned and crisp.
Remove chicken; drain on paper towels. Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken before serving.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: egg custard(club member: brad smith)
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Shake pie to see if it is done in center.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook 2 tablespoons butter, onion and celery until clear.
Mix chicken broth and mashed, cooked cauliflower with first 3 ingredients.
Put flour in melted butter; mix.
Take off stove and add cream.
Cook until thick.
Add to all other ingredients.
Cook all together and serve in bread bowls.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes in skillet with 2 tablespoons butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Fry until potatoes are done.
Use medium heat.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix 1st three ingredients and pour in churn.
Fill the rest of churn with 2% or whole milk.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix with water.
Drop in hot oil.

title: tomato and mushroom salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, mushrooms and onions.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour over and stir.
Chill for a couple of hours before serving.

title: asparagus with sesame butter
directions: Place asparagus spears in a large skillet; add boiling water and salt.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender.
Remove asparagus and keep warm.
Drain cooking liquid, reserving 1/2 cup in a small saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and cold water; stir into liquid.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in butter until melted.
Spoon over asparagus; sprinkle with sesame seed and serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macho cheese casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush cheese chips on bottom of pan. Mix chicken breasts, soups, chilies and sour cream; layer over chips.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at
400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bran rolls(makes 16)
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except unbleached flour.
Let it sit under cover for several hours.
Gradually add unbleached flour, kneading dough until it is smooth.
Let it rise for 2 hours.
Punch down, divide in 16 pieces.
Roll each and place on cookie sheet. Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Work flour, salt and shortening together until mixture is like coarse meal.
Beat egg and water together and add to flour mixture, mixing well.
Divide into portions.
Roll portions very thin and cut into narrow strips, then into short pieces.
Drop into boiling broth.
Simmer a few minutes, then add the 1/2 cup milk.
Heat well, but do not allow to boil.
May add black pepper.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan.
Add peanut butter, sugar and cracker crumbs.
Mix and press into pan.
Melt Hershey bar and pour over top.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in small bowl; blend in sugar and melted margarine. Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into wedges.
Serve topped with ice cream and hot fudge sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package.
Let cool and crumble in large bowl.
Pour milk over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crumble candy bars on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out all water.
Stir all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and blend.
Sift dry ingredients 2 or 3 times; add to mixture, blending thoroughly. Add carrots, small amounts at a time; blend well.
Bake for 1 hour in tube pan at 350°.
(Grease and flour pan before pouring cake mixture into it.)

title: nana's lima beans
directions: Cook lima beans as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter over low heat;
add salt and pepper.
Blend in flour and remove from heat.
Add milk and then return to a medium heat,
stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Add
cubed cheese (cube 3/4 of the cheese) and stir. Cheese
does not
have
to
melt.
Remove
from
heat.
Layer macaroni
and cheese
sauce;
if sauce is too thick, then add more
milk, in Dutch oven or roasting pan.
Take the remaining cheese
and
slice thinly.
Place
on top of the macaroni and cheese sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked chicken with italiano
directions: Combine Parmesan, parsley, oregano, garlic and pepper; mix well.
Dip chicken breasts into butter, then into cheese mixture to coat well.
Place in a large shallow baking dish.
Drizzle any remaining margarine over chicken breasts.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve at once.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Generously grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Soak the chicken in 2 c. cold water with 2 tsp. salt for 20 minutes. Drain, rinse off and pat dry. Place in a baking pan (the chicken should fit tightly in pan). Mix all the other ingredients together and pour over chicken; let sit for 20 minutes. Bake at 400° on the lower oven rack until tender. Remove from oven, cover the pan and let sit for 15 minutes. Serve on rice or noodles.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes with ham.
Cook onion and celery separately until tender.
Add to potatoes.
Add butter and milk.
Add grated cheese for topping.

title: salmon stew
directions: Put milk and canned milk in heavy 4-quart pan.
Add butter or margarine.
Heat until real hot, but not boiling.
Debone salmon; remove skin.
Crumble salmon real good.
Add to milk mixture. Leave heat on for a few minutes, but do not boil.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve with saltine crackers or oyster crackers.

title: depression day gravy
directions: Place margarine in pan.
Melt, then stir in flour, cocoa powder, sugar and salt.
Add milk and stir over medium heat until thick as desired.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour; mix.
Spread 3/4 batter on a greased and floured cookie sheet, 18 x 12 x 1-inch.
Make it a little higher on the sides of the pan.
Spread 2 cans of pie filling over all.
Drop the remaining batter here and there over all.
It spreads and makes its own design when baked.

title: cinnamon cutouts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheet. In large bowl, cream brown sugar, butter, egg and vanilla.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine milk, flour and sugar and mix thoroughly; add to the melted margarine. Add peaches and do not stir.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes or until browned.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy vegetable ham soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan. Add broth, milk and cheese. Stir in vegetables, ham and pepper; cover.
Cook until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Layer in glass 13 x 9-inch dish. Chill and serve with Fritos scoops corn chips.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients, then add the last five and mix well.
Pour into two greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Cans will be about half full.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and lay cans on their sides for ten minutes, then remove.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain hearts.
Keep water from hearts in a separate dish. Mash hearts.
Add bread crumbs, garlic, cheese and oil.
Mix egg with artichoke water.
Mix all together and press into pan. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix butter, flour and nuts and press in pan for crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and pour into cooled crust.
Mix 7-Up, cornstarch, sugar and Jell-O and cook until thick.
Cool and add peaches and pour on top of pie.

title: quick pan rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg and shortening.
Add one cup of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Continue stirring until smooth.
Scrape batter from sides of bowl.
Cover.
Let dough rise in warm place until double in size, about 30 minutes.
Stir down batter.
Turn onto floured surface.
Divide into 12 equal parts. Shape each into smooth ball with lightly greased fingers.
Place in a greased square pan.
Let rise until double the size.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: In a saucepan, bring to a boil the water and margarine. Remove from heat and stir in flour. Using a wooden spoon, mix until smooth and soft batter forms. Cool for 5 minutes; add eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each egg. After fourth egg is added, keep stirring until no sign of fluid remains. Using a rubber spatula, spread batter into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch flat baking pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Cool completely. In large mixing bowl using a hand mixer, combine milk and pudding until pudding starts to set. Mix in cream cheese. Using spatula, spread mixture over crust, letting edges show. Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding. Top with chocolate fudge. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil margarine, hot water and cocoa; then add to flour and sugar mixture.
Add soda, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Bake on cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Drain juice from pineapple; do not drain juice completely dry.
Add pineapple, diced or miniature marshmallows and diced bananas; mix all ingredients well.
Line sheet pan with vanilla wafers.
Pour in mixture.
Crumble remaining wafers and spread on top.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, with portable electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter with peanut butter. Add the sugars gradually; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture; beat at low speed until well combined. Refrigerate dough, covered, until chilled, about 1 hour.
With teaspoon, shape dough into balls about 3/4-inch in diameter. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork, making crisscross pattern.
Bake for 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand a few minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: monkey-ball cake
directions: Put 1 cup sugar and butter or margarine in pot on stove and melt on low while preparing other ingredients.
Grease Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Use 4 cans of refrigerated rolls (10 in each can).
Open 2 cans of rolls.
Cut each roll into quarters.
Shake in a Tupperware bowl with lid on 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Place balls in Bundt pan and pour 1/2 of solution over balls.
Repeat the same with next 2 cans of rolls and add more cinnamon to the Tupperware bowl mixture, if needed, then pour the rest of the solution on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk. Add nuts and bananas.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jacque's barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in a large pan.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar and enough water to cover.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until meat is tender. Drain.
This part may be done the day before or early the same day.
Blend cornstarch and water together.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 3 minutes.
Cook ribs on grill, basting and turning frequently until done.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine water chestnuts, onion, chicken, celery, lemon juice, mayonnaise and 1/2 c. grated cheese and place in 1 qt. casserole dish.

title: vegetable-burger soup
directions: Cook beef in a heavy 3 qt. saucepan until browned, stirring to crumble;
drain off drippings.
Stir in remaining ingredients, and bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: picnic macaroni salad
directions: Cook rotini according to directions.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
In a large bowl, combine salad dressing, onion, sugar, relish and mustard; blend well.
Stir in rotini, peas and eggs. Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Boil rice.
Cook broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine rice, broccoli, onion, soup and water.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Arrange in casserole.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Cook in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: jam kolaches
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese in medium bowl.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoon jam on each cookie. Fold opposite sides together.
Press edges with fork tongs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas #2
directions: Boil chicken; let cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Saute onions and chilies in oil.
Add salt, cumin, diced chicken and broth, then simmer.
In separate bowl, combine soup and sour cream.
Add 1/2 of this mixture to simmering chicken.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add oil and vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 baking dish with Pam; pour evenly in the bottom of the baking dish 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup coconut. Set aside. Mix cake mix exactly as directed on cake box. Pour batter evenly over the nuts and coconut in baking dish. Set aside. Combine butter (or oleo) and cream cheese and microwave until butter is melted and cream cheese is nearly all melted. Mix until smooth. Next stir in powdered sugar (a little at a time) until all is mixed well with the cream cheese/butter mixture. Stir until this combination is smooth. Pour this mixture over top of cake mix, pecans and coconut. Bake at 350° until toothpick in cake comes out clean or 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut loin in half. Salt and pepper both pieces of pork.
Wrap each in separate piece of foil.
Put meat thermometer in each piece, being careful to wrap foil back around the thermometer. Bake until it reads 185° to 190°, well done. Pour liquid off of loins.
Open foil and let tops brown about 10 minutes longer.

title: pie crust - always ready mixture
directions: Mix well with pastry cutter and refrigerate.
Dip out by cupful as needed.
Add 3 tablespoons ice water to 1 heaping of crust mixture.

title: oven cooked rice
directions: Mix together in 1-quart casserole and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kipplens
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, vanilla, pecans and salt. Mix well.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
You can roll slightly cooled cookies in confectioners sugar or eat plain.

title: roman holiday
directions: Cook spaghetti very few minutes.
Add to all other ingredients and bake slowly (about 300°) approximately 2 hours.

title: pumpkin ginger pie
directions: Pour milk in large bowl.
Add pie filling.
Beat 1 minute or until blended.
Let stand until thickened.
Stir in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and spice.
Spread mixture into crust.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer. Let stand 20 to 30 minutes to soften.
Garnish with dollops of topping and strawberries.

title: savory hot butter sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat.
Serve hot with fish or shellfish.

title: kranz cake
directions: Make cake, icing and praline.

title: baked dressing
directions: Tear bread into pieces.
Saute the onion and celery in oleo. Add together the cream of chicken soup, water, egg and sage.
Mix together the bread and sauteed ingredients to the soup mixture. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cream dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Pat mixture into bottom of 9 X 13 baking pan.
In a separate bowl, combine condensed milk, sour cream, and lemon juice.
Evenly spread the milk and cream cheese mixture over the crust.
Gently spoon on apple pie filling. Sprinkle pecans and cinnamon over pie filling.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: poor man's steak
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Pat mixture on a cookie sheet, refrigerate overnight.
Cut into 6 squares, roll each square in flour and brown in large skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peachy bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, wheat bran, sugar and baking powder and stir to mix well; set aside.
Drain peaches (save juice) and puree in blender.
Add juice to pureed peaches to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add peach puree and egg whites to flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Fold in dried peaches or pecans.
Coat muffin cups with Pam and fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheese dollars
directions: Mix all ingredients in a ball; roll out.
Cut out with a floured glass.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add sauce. Simmer 10 minutes.
Put in dish.
Add cheese and be sure you flake biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: pizza soup
directions: Make soup according to the directions on the can. Add remaining ingredients and simmer. The longer you cook, the thicker the soup. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese when served.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve gelatin in water.
Combine pineapple and cherry juices to measure 2 1/2 cups.
Add along with lemon juice to gelatin.
Divide gelatin in half.
Set half of gelatin aside and chill other half until partially set.
Fold pineapple into chilled gelatin; pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until almost firm.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg.
In a small mixing bowl, combine the milk, egg, sugar and melted margarine.
Add orange juice, rind, chopped apples (skins may be left on) and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir into milk mixture with a spoon until blended. Do not overbeat.
Preheat oil in a skillet to 350°.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn so they brown evenly.
Allow to cool.

title: boiled water
directions: Pour water into pot.
Cover with lid.
Place pot on stove burner; wait until 3 minutes of your time has been used.
If water is not getting hot, check to see if burner is on.
Don't watch too closely as a watched pot never boils.
When water is ready, use as needed.
If your first efforts are unsuccessful, try again.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Mix green pepper, onion, soups, tomatoes and chili powder.
In bottom of a greased baking pan, put a layer of tortillas, layer of chicken and layer of soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: elizabeth's fudge pie
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
butter.
Add
eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla
and nuts.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 30 minutes starting in a cold oven.
Delicious served with peppermint ice cream.

title: raspberry pudding
directions: Mix sugar, butter, flour, salt, baking powder and milk and pour into a greased pan.
Batter will be thick.
Mix raspberries, sugar and butter; pour over top of batter.
Pour boiling water over top of all.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: end-of-garden pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, peppers, cabbage, onions and tomatoes in salt water overnight (1/2 cup salt to 2 quarts water).
Drain in the morning.
Cook carrots and string beans, which have been cut into 1 inch pieces, in water until tender; drain well.
Mix soaked and cooked vegetables with remaining ingredients and boil for 10 minutes.
Place in sterilized jars and seal at once.
This is very colorful and delicious.

title: fluffy potato bake
directions: Cook, peel and mash the potatoes.
In a saucepan, cook onion in 1/4 cup margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir onion, cottage cheese, parsley and salt into mashed potatoes.
Spoon potato mixture into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Drizzle melted margarine over top, if desired.
Bake at 350° until mixture is heated through and browned, about 30 minutes.
Garnish the potato casserole with additional snipped parsley, if desired.

title: pecan icebox pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar and baking powder. Add broken up crackers (grated fine).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 inch pie plate that has been greased and floured.
Bake 20-25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Whip cream until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Spread on pie.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Store in refrigerator 1-2 hours.

title: nacho casserole
directions: In a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish, spread uncooked rice in bottom.
In skillet, brown meat and drain.
Stir in corn, tomatoes, taco seasoning mix and water.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture over rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with tortilla chips, then cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sara's simple "spaghetti" salmon soup
directions: In a large pot, heat on high 1 1/2 quarts water.
Once boiling, add Ramen noodles; reduce heat to keep water at a slow boil.
Add salmon and carrots.
Continue to cook for 3 to 5 minutes; if noodles bubble up, either reduce heat or add frozen vegetables.
If not, then add frozen vegetables and cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add contents of 2 packages of seasonings that accompany the noodles, or less to reduce salt intake.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers.
Make pudding with milk according to package directions.
Fold into Cool Whip.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cover the bottom of a casserole dish with a thin layer of enchilada sauce, add a layer of flour tortillas so the bottom of the dish is covered but the tortillas are not overlapping (tear them to fit as needed).
Cover this with a layer of chicken, onions, olives, and cheese.
Place tortillas over this and cover with enchilada sauce.
Continue to layer in this manner until all ingredients are used (the exact amount of ingredients can be tailored to suit your preferences).
Finish with a layer of tortillas and top with enchilada sauce and sprinkle cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered for 1 hour or until hot and bubbly.
(For a meat free variation, you can substitute a can of black beans, drained, or a can of refried beans for the chicken.)

title: easy waldorf stew
directions: Arrange meat and vegetables in large pot in the order listed. (Do not brown stew meat.)
Over top, sprinkle sugar, salt, pepper and tapioca.
Cover with tomato soup and add 1/4 can of water only and pour over top.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours, stirring once or twice while baking.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan. Place coconut and pecans on bottom. Make cake mix according to directions.
Pour over ingredients.

title: jam buns (tarts)
directions: Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in 3-inch squares.
Put dab of jam in center, less than 1 teaspoon.
Fold corners into center.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Serves up to 4 people.

title: spinach-cheese squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix all remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over butter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before cutting.

title: calico beans
directions: Cut bacon and brown with beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Drain half of liquid from lima beans.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, covered, or crock-pot on high for 3 hours.

title: chocolate chip mandel bread
directions: Combine in a large bowl, eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Add salt and vanilla. Add flour slowly and mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease hands.
Place on a cookie sheet in 4 equal loaves. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Slice and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
all
but
the margarine, evaporated milk and brown sugar, together in a big bowl and stir to combine.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 12 cup tube or Bundt pan.	Bake 90 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on box.
Mix in the cottage cheese, Cool Whip and strawberries.
Place in refrigerator and allow to congeal.

title: walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, condensed milk, egg, cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoonful each of ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: greek salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Break up Feta cheese and add to vegetables.
Add seasonings and olive oil.
Toss well.
Makes eight good-size servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas, then dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: pork chops and wild rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Salt and pepper pork chops.
In a skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Add chops; cook 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until brown.
Combine rice mix and boiling water. Pour rice mixture into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place chops on top of rice.
Cover; bake about 40 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: red snapper
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Spray a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch glass baking dish with a nonfat cooking spray.
Combine all the ingredients together in a glass dish except fish, shrimp, and wine.
Microwave on High, covered with wax paper, all the ingredients until vegetables are tender (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Stir in shrimp and wine.
Place fish fillets on top of the mixture; spoon some of the mixture over fish.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: For 10 x 4 1/2-inch bowl.
Cook potatoes, then chunk.
Mix sugar, mustard and salad dressing thoroughly.
Add diced potatoes, eggs (chopped), and onions.
Layer in bowl.
Stir to mix together. Save 15 slices of eggs for top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: raspberry carousel
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry juice cocktail and chill until thickened.
Fold in apple, celery and nuts.
Spoon into a 5 cup mold and chill until set.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining crackers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili and hominy casserole
directions: Combine chili and beans.
Saute onions and add to chili and beans.
Cook hominy down in oil.
Add to other mixture.
Cook until bubbling at 350°.

title: campfire stew(method:  one pot)
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
In large pot, brown hamburger with onion and green pepper, stirring continuously to break up hamburger into small pieces.
Add vegetable soup and can of water. Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix Junket tablets and water until tablets dissolve.
Add mixtures together. Pour into ice cream maker and add milk.
Use crushed ice and rock salt to harden.

title: blueberry fish pond
directions: You will also need cups and spoons.

title: angel tea ring
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cook until thick.
Have gelatin ready, dissolved in cup of cold water.
Add to hot mixture.
When cool, add vanilla, lemon extract and cream that has been whipped. Cut angel food cake in half and put mixture between halves and over all of cake as if to ice.
Serve plain or sprinkle with coconut.
Make and refrigerate the day before serving.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: white trash
directions: Mix, melt and slow cook the first 3 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour first mixture over second and put in a large brown paper bag.
Pour in 1 box xxxx sugar and shake until coated.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then make patties 4 x 1/2-inch. Brown in Teflon frypan.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Easiest to handle on piece of wax paper.
Can freeze on a cookie sheet and store in large Tupperware container.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour and shortening.
Mix well until resembles coarse meal. Add milk. Stir until well blended.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead 3 to 4 times.
Roll into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage (at room temperature) over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch margin on all sides.
Carefully roll dough lengthwise, jellyroll fashion.
Pinch ends to seal.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Place 1-inch apart on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry sour cream jello
directions: Mix 1 small raspberry Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
When Jell-O is dissolved add 1 small can crushed pineapple, 1 carton raspberries with juice and 2 cups crushed pecans.
Pour into flat baking dish.
When mixture is firm, spread sour cream (a thick layer) over top, then repeat first Jell-O layer on top of sour cream.

title: apple butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure all ingredients into large bowl.
Beat at low speed until moistened, then at medium for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Spread with Lemon Cheese Frosting.

title: blackberry sour cream pie
directions: Place berries in shell.
Combine 1 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream, stirring well.
Spoon over berries.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and
1/2 cup flour and cut in butter until mixture is coarse like meal.
Sprinkle evenly over sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Garnish with blackberries and mint leaves (optional).

title: terri's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cut package of cookie dough in half after unwrapping.
Cut each half into 5 slices and cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Drop each piece into greased mini muffin cup.
Bake according to package directions or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and immediately press peanut butter cup into each cookie.
When chocolate starts to melt slightly, sprinkle with chopped pecans. When completely cooled, remove from pans.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni according to directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water 3 times.
Keep covered with cold water until ready to use.
Melt butter or margarine.
Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Watch carefully so it won't scorch.
Turn heat to low and add the Velveeta cheese.
Cut cheese into small cubes before adding.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add minced onion and salt to taste.
Add the cooked macaroni.
Pour into 2 large casserole dishes.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in about 2 cups of water until tender.
Add salt.
Add milk and cheese, a little at a time, then add sour cream and mix together.
Put in pan and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey breast scallopini
directions: Pat the cutlets dry.
Mix the Parmesan and bread crumbs. Press the mixture into both sides of cutlets.
Heat 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet.
Add the breast, brown on both sides.
Cook about 5 minutes on each side.
Transfer to a warm platter.
Add lemon juice to pan, scrape the browned bits into sauce.
Add the remaining spoon of butter.
Pour over cutlets, serve immediately.

title: date delight
directions: Cook until thick; spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry icebox cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; beat in sugar a little at a time to make meringue like.
Beat in vanilla and cream of tartar.
Fold in the 3 cups crushed saltine crackers.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and spread in meringue/cracker mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
After cake is cooled, top with Cool Whip and cover that with the cherry pie filling. Refrigerate.

title: sweet soy sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan; mix well.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard star anise.
Set aside to cool.
Pour cooled sauce into a sterilized jar with a tight fitting lid.
It's good for about 6 months if put in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: microwave dried apples
directions: Peel and core apples; cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Arrange on microwave roasting rack.
Microwave 18 to 22 minutes or until limp and slightly moist.
Place apples slices on wire rack and let stand overnight.
One medium apple yields approximately 1/2 cup dried apples.

title: saute green beans
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add milk with flour beaten in. Pour in green beans, salt and pepper.
Toss and shake over a hot fire for five minutes.
Serve hot.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream egg, butter, sugar and vanilla; add soda and flour. Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 4 sections and form loaf.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Then slice thin and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 can of onion rings with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.

title: taco seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl until evenly distributed.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 400° until puffy and brown.

title: ham quiche
directions: Place ham in bottom of pie shell; top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, garlic powder, lemon juice, chopped chives, onion, salt and pepper together until well blended.
Pour into shell over ham and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Add salt and pepper.
Then add vegetables.
Mix butter, flour and milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust browns.

title: mexican casserole(makes 8 servings.)
directions: Put ground beef in skillet and brown. Let simmer until done. Add chopped onion and salt. Add chili to tomato soup.
Let simmer while stirring. Mixture should be consistency of gravy. If dry, add small amount of water. Line large casserole with 1/2 of Fritos, then rest of Fritos on top.
Sprinkle cheese and catsup on top. Bake in 400° oven until cheese is melted. Serve hot.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring Karo, margarine, sugar and salt to a boil and boil for 4 1/2 minutes.
Remove and add soda and 1 teaspoon of margarine. Pour syrup over popped corn and nuts and mix well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: sour cream-apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat together sour cream, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Add apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Combine, brown sugar, 1/3 cup flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of pie filling. Bake for 25 minutes more.
Serve hot or cold.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Boil veal in water for 5 minutes. Drain. Brown veal lightly in a frying pan, then add all other ingredients.
Simmer slowly until peppers are tender and meat is done to your satisfaction.

title: chickin mit sauerkraut
directions: Cook meat and drain off fat.
Mix meat, soup, sauerkraut and garlic powder.
Heat and simmer.

title: cold weather soup
directions: Begin cooking vegetables according to package directions.
Add meat and other ingredients immediately.
Cook until potatoes are done and onion tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to desired thickness.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in large heavy saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic and sausage.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir in rice, chicken broth, Tabasco sauce, tomatoes and seasoning.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat and let sit 5 minutes longer before fluffing with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: broiled venison steaks
directions: Rub the steaks with salt, pepper and a little mustard. Preheat broiler and place steaks about 5-inches below the heat on a well-greased grill.
About 7 to 10 minutes on each side should be sufficient for rare, 15 minutes for medium and 20 minutes for well-done.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: In a large bowl, mix together turkey, the two cheeses and cooked sauteed onions.
Coat the mixture with enchilada sauce just to cover.
Warm tortillas over the stove burner, turning once. Then dip in enchilada sauce and place a couple tablespoons of turkey mixture and roll tortilla over.
In a 4 x 8-inch pan, put a little enchilada sauce in the bottom.
Place filled tortillas in pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: puff pizza
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Put in bowl.
Add pizza sauce and stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add grated cheese, cooked hamburger or sausage, pepperoni, mushrooms, onions, black olives, green peppers, etc.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients in large bowl until combined well. Put in 10-inch or 6-cup deep dish pie plate.
In a bowl combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and butter until resembles a coarse meal.
Add boiling water and mix (forms a dough).
Drop over blueberry mixture and bake on a baking sheet in middle of preheated 400° oven, 30 to 40 minutes, until topping is golden.
Serve warm with French vanilla frozen yogurt or ice cream.

title: applesauce spice loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg alternately with the combined applesauce and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in the pecans.
Bake in a moderate oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, until a cake tester inserted in the center comes
away clean.
Remove to rack.
When cool, wrap in foil.
Slice the next day or freeze.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Pour butter in a large, flat pan; shake potatoes in dry mixture.
Layer potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn over and cook until done.

title: ecstasies
directions: Mix first six ingredients in order given.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put Hershey bars on top immediately after removing from oven.
Let melt; spread and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook cake in pan 15 minutes, then prick with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Meanwhile, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and carefully pour over warm cake.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken feed
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion, mushrooms, garlic and 1/4 teaspoon thyme in butter. Stir in the chicken, gravy, bouillon and pepper. Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Microwave sweet chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in a large microwavable bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and rest of the milk until well blended.
Refrigerate 10 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with chocolate syrup drizzled lightly over top and drop additional Cool Whip by spoonfuls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut the broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Fry bacon until crisp and break into bite size pieces.
Toss all of the ingredients together.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine dressing, cranberries and onion soup mix.
Stir together to make a sauce.
Place chicken pieces in a baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: minted-glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and add honey and butter. Cook over low heat until carrots are glazed, turning several times.
Just before serving, sprinkle with mint.

title: cafe adrian baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut sliver off top, flat side.
Scoop out centers into bowl.
Add everything.
Beat with mixer until blended.
It won't be real smooth.
If needed, add a little hot milk.
Put back in shells.
Heat in regular oven until hot and crispy.
Really good.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Put into Pyrex pie plate (deep).
For topping, put small marshmallows on top.
Put in oven at 325° and let marshmallows brown.
You have to watch because they will burn fast.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust.
Cover with top crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: frosting for chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo with milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat and add sugar and vanilla.
Put on cake while still hot.

title: strawberry thrill salad
directions: Mix water with Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Chill for several hours or overnight. Mix room temperature cream cheese with sour cream, vanilla and sugar.
Spread over chilled Jell-O mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: chili
directions: Put enough cooking oil in pan to cook onions.
Fry them until tender.
Add ground beef to onions and cook meat until it is done, stirring continuously.
Drain excess fat off of onions and meat. Add all other ingredients, stirring continuously, until it begins to boil.
Lower heat; cover and let simmer about 5 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Make up pie crust dough enough for top and bottom layers for an 11 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate until cold. Roll out enough dough for bottom of pan, saving 1/2 for top of pie.

title: soy sauce rump roast
directions: Rub salt, celery salt, paprika, black pepper and garlic salt (not much) or onion salt into a rump roast.
Then cover the roast with soy sauce.
Let brown at 400°, then turn down to 250°.

title: boiled cookie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, bring to a boil, 1 minute, stirring constantly.
While hot, add peanut butter cooking oats & vanilla.
Stir to blend well.
Drop by tsp. on wax paper.
Ready to eat when cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs together.
Sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Add the mixtures together and mix well.
Add the coconut, carrots and nuts. Pour mixture into 9 x 13 pan and bake 1 hour at 300° or 2 round cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: sour pickles
directions: Using an egg beater, mix all ingredients, except cucumbers, in large crock. Add cucumbers, making sure to sink them in the brine. Put a plate with a rock on top to keep cukes submerged. Let cukes sit in brine 2 to 3 weeks, preferably longer. You can add a pinch of alum to the brine to keep pickles crisp. Pack in jars or you can just leave in crock and eat at your leisure. Makes 4 to 5 quarts.

title: he-man hamburgers
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into hamburger patties.
Cook about 5 minutes on each side or until browned.

title: punch(sugar-free)
directions: Add enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, sugar and melted butter.
Pat into oblong dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Combine jello and water, then add cream cheese, pineapple and coconut.
Let congeal before serving.

title: aunt sis' banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs; add milk, salt, baking powder, baking soda, bananas and vanilla; mix together. Add the flour; beat until mixed well.
Add 1 cup nuts (your choice).
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf, 2 regular or 4 small loaves.
For small, bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: sweet potato, cranberry bake
directions: Mix the flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon.
Cut in the margarine like pie crust.
Mix 1 cup of the crumb mixture with the yams and cranberries.
Sprinkle the rest of the crumbs on top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and sour cream.
Batter will be stiff.
Grease two 9-inch pans.
Place batter in pan.
Combine topping ingredients and sprinkle over batter.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and soda.
Add mayonnaise, cold water and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: canned pickles(crisp pickle slices-bread and butter type)
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours (can stand longer, if necessary), drain well.

title: settlers beans
directions: Brown ground chuck with onions. Drain fat. Cook bacon and break into tiny pieces. If you don't want this dish with meat, either one or both meats can be omitted.
Add beans and rest of ingredients. Heat in slow cooker for 1 1/2 hours on low. Can serve in a slow cooker, too.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Preheat
oven to 450°.
Peel potatoes and cut into long strips about
1/2-inch
wide.
Dry strips thoroughly on paper towels. Toss
in
a bowl with oil as if making a salad.
When strips are thoroughly coated with oil, spread them in a single layer on
a cookie
sheet
and place in preheated oven for 35 minutes.
Turn strips periodically to brown on all sides.
If a
crisper, browner potato is desired, run under broiler for 1 minute
or
two. Sprinkle with salt before serving.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains 80 calories per serving.

title: rondele
directions: Blend and refrigerate at least two hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: dressing for slaw
directions: Mix and pour over slaw.

title: chesley's baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and saut onions in bacon grease.
Add other ingredients to skillet, making a sauce.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday ham rolls
directions: Do not separate rolls. Slice top from rolls in one piece. Leaving bottoms in the foil pan, layer ham and cheese on rolls. Replace tops. Combine butter, poppy seed, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion flakes; mix well. Drizzle over rolls. Refrigerate until butter is firm. Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 20 minutes. Cut into small pieces. Good served hot or cold. Serves 12.

title: tofu patties
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in oil until soft.
Drain tofu; mash it with a fork and mix in with egg, flour, salt and soy sauce.
Add vegetables and curry or cheese.
Form into patties; cover with wheat germ or corn meal and griddle until done or bake at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 the cheese.
Mix and bake at 350° until bubbly.
Remove; sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top, then brown in oven.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook the spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain and set aside.
Saute green pepper and onion in margarine until tender. Add the tomatoes and stir until slightly thickened.
Cut the cheese into chunks and melt in the tomatoes. Stir well to prevent sticking. Add the Worcestershire sauce, salt and red pepper. Remove from heat.
Add the peas, mushrooms and chicken. Blend well. Stir in the spaghetti.
Pour this into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 1/2 gallon.
This dish freezes well.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Cook ground meat until brown and done.
Add onion and pepper and simmer.
Add chili spice and mix.
Stir and simmer.
Will need to add 1/2 cup water.
Add tomato sauce on tomatoes.
Stir well. Heat beans in large stew pan and add mixture.
Simmer for 30 minutes, covered.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Can serve over spaghetti; kids love it.

title: harmonious day
directions: Measure words carefully.
Add heaping cups of understanding to milk of human kindness and sift together 3 times before using. Make a smooth sauce, not too thick.
Use generous amounts of time and patience.
Cook with gas on front burner.
Keep temperature low; do not boil.
Add a dash of dry humor and a pinch of warm personality with individual molds.
Works best when made by a good mixer.

title: suki aiki
directions: Brown meat and other ingredients except the onion.
After browning meat, add onion that is sliced.
Cook very slightly until onion appears slightly clear in appearance.
Pour over rice and shake on soy sauce.

title: orange lamb shanks
directions: In a 10-inch skillet or 3-quart saucepan, brown the lamb shanks in hot oil; drain off excess fat.
Combine the orange peel, orange juice, teriyaki sauce, garlic and curry powder; pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Skim fat from pan juices.
Serve meat and pan juices over rice.
Garnish with quartered orange slices, snipped parsley and a green onion fan, if desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix and let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove and let cool.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Grease the casserole; place a layer of crumbs, well moistened with sauce; stir with fork to see that all crumbs are moistened. Layer cheese, grated eggs and grated pimento.
Repeat the layers; again stir with fork until all crumbs are moistened (the pudding will be dry unless crumbs are moistened).
You may have to add milk to be sure crumbs are moistened.
Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in medium saucepan.
Add milk.
Heat until boiling for three minutes.
Add margarine and peanut butter; stir well.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.

title: strawberry nut pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix ingredients well, about 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes (I only bake mine around 40 minutes; keep testing).
Let cool 10 minutes before inverting on plate.
Cover cake with Handi-Wrap. When cooled, frost cake with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together in a 3-quart saucepan, the sugars and flour and then add water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add the margarine and vanilla and stir until the margarine is melted.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef, then add tomatoes and water.
Then add all other ingredients and cook for 45 minutes hard.
Then simmer for 30 minutes on a lower heat.

title: quick and easy pig picking sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and simmer until sugar melts.

title: brownie cake
directions: Combine oleo, water and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Add flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix with beater, then add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in large cookie sheet 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pralines #2
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat 8 to 9 minutes. After it comes to rolling boil, remove from heat and beat until thickened.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain
beets,
reserve
cup liquid. Cook together, sugar, cornstarch, margarine, vinegar and beet juice and salt. Stir constantly until thickened; add beets and cook 5 minutes, covered, on medium heat.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Add salt and pepper, vinegar, brown sugar and catsup.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: casserole tyson
directions: Put all ingredients into a large oven casserole and mix well. Add mushrooms last.
Cover casserole and bake in a 325° oven for 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: tortilla chip hot dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in a glass pie dish.
Spread can chili over cheese.
Spread taco sauce over mixture.
Sprinkle shredded cheese, to taste.
Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: penuche coconut bars
directions: Blend shortening and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add 1 cup flour and the salt.
Stir in milk.
Pat evenly in lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.
Beat eggs; add 1 cup brown sugar and vanilla and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread over baked crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into 36 squares.

title: pecan nut cups
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, flour and butter by hand until dough does not stick to sides of bowl.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Take dough from refrigerator and shape into miniature muffin tins as shells.
Do not grease tins.
Put a spoonful of nut filling into each shell.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool in tins; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into the crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add chops and brown.
Remove chops and set aside.
Cook garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Add sliced tomatoes, wine and seasonings.
Lay chops on top; cover and cook for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes immersed in boiling water for 30 - 45 minutes or until tender. Let cool to touch; peel and mash potatoes. Combine potatoes, brown sugar, and next 4 ingredients; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Spoon into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in oil or butter.
Add the flour and curry; stir.
Gradually add the broth, then the pumpkin, honey and other seasonings to taste.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cream and heat through without boiling.
Top with a dollop of sour cream, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream roll
directions: Make cake as directed. Line 2 oblong pans with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes. Remove wax paper from pan. Cool again 5 minutes. Spoon ice cream on and roll as jelly roll. Wrap in aluminum foil. Freeze for 6 hours.

title: teriyaki pork roast
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a greased slow cooker. Add roast and turn to coat. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours or until a thermometer instead into the roast reads 160°. Remove roast and keep warm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients including sugar into large bowl.
Make a well and add all other ingredients except pecans.
Mix until smooth.
Add pecans.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: chili dip
directions: Put chili with no beans in a pan.
Heat upon stove.
Put cream cheese in and stir until melted in with chili.
Put the Mexican sauce and black olives in also.
Stir until completely mixed up, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast(saltim bocca)
directions: On each chicken breast, place a slice of cheese, sprinkle of sage, one slice Prosciutto and a little tomato sauce.
Roll chicken breasts and secure with toothpicks.
Roll in melted butter, then in bread crumbs that have been mixed with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until browned.
Serves 4.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all together and serve as a dip.

title: marinated kale
directions: Place oil at bottom of large saucepan.
Heat slightly.
Cut leaves of kale.
Throw away stems.
Place kale in oil with 1 to 2 tablespoons of water.
Cover.
(Check frequently, keep adding water.)
Drain marinade of artichokes into saucepan.
(Cut some artichoke in with kale).
Cover.
Check frequently, adding water when needed.
Add 1 tablespoon of Ken's dressing; cook.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid as per directions on package.
Pour into prepared mixture of pineapple and orange juice.
Allow ingredients to chill.
Add ginger ale and sherbet just before serving.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; make into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix brownie mix, water, oil and egg.
Beat by hand 50 strokes. Add frosting and sour cream.
Mix well; spread into pan; sprinkle pecans and chips on top.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely, cut into bars.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute mushrooms and onion until onion is soft.
Mix together flour, black and cayenne pepper, salt, Mrs. Dash and garlic powder in a bowl.
Lightly bread chicken breasts in flour mixture.
Brown chicken on both sides in butter, adding extra butter, if needed.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes until sauce thickens.

title: miss connie's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Set overnight.
Add other ingredients and mix together and serve.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 3 eggs, cheese, sugar and vanilla and pour on top of cake layer.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take out centers of mushrooms.
Stuff center of mushrooms with sausage.
Pour spaghetti sauce over mushrooms.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1/2 hour.
With approximately 10 minutes left, sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients very fine; put in big soup pot with olive oil.
Saute until golden; then add tomatoes (or paste) and cook again for about 3 minutes.
Add hot water, salt and beans; bring to a good boil.
Let simmer, covered, for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese calzone
directions: Roll bread dough into large rectangle.
Mix cheeses, egg and parsley.
Spread onto bread, keeping away from edges.
Fold dough around cheese.
Moisten edges to seal.
Bake on cookie sheet 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with pizza sauce for dipping.

title: bar-b-q's
directions: Cook hamburger and onion.
Add corned beef, brown sugar, catsup, vinegar and chili powder.
Mix well and simmer for approximately 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients into 16 meat balls. Brown in shortening.
Combine rest of ingredients and add meatballs. Cook for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cheese until creamy; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in paper lined muffin pan.
Pour cheese over wafer, filling cups full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These are best if left in pans and refrigerated overnight.
Top with fresh fruit or leave plain.

title: dressing for slaw
directions: Mix together and toss over a head of shredded cabbage.

title: pork chops and corn
directions: Brown chops quickly on both sides and place in casserole. Cover with other ingredients which have been mixed well.
Pour over all 1 cup milk.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: ham and asparagus roll-ups
directions: Blot ham with paper towel to remove moisture.
Spread a thin layer of cream cheese over each slice of ham.
Roll asparagus spear in each piece of ham.
No need for toothpicks.
The cream cheese will hold everything in place.
Cut in 2-inch lengths.

title: ooey-gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Pat in bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana or pumpkin or zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean (about an hour).

title: mama's minestrone
directions: Bring to boil and simmer on low 15-20 minutes all ingredients except peas, and macaroni,
until veggies are crisp-tender.
Add; peas and macaroni.
Simmer another 12-15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: holly punch
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat to a boil; simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Serve.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 9x13x2 baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Beat oleo or butter in a large mixing bowl with electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar and beat until well combined.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: taco hot dish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix taco seasoning and ground beef.
Set aside.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise.
Set aside.
Mix Bisquick and water.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan with a wet spoon.
Layer in order: ground beef mixture, sour cream mixture, green peppers, onion, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, then paprika. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and edges are bubbly.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all into a pot and cook on low for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: watermelon granita
directions: In food processor
fitted
with the steel blade or in a blender, in batches,
puree
the
watermelon and transfer to a bowl.
In a
stainless steel or enameled saucepan, combine the sugar, lime juice, lime
rind and water; bring the liquid to a boil, stirring to
dissolve sugar.
Simmer syrup for 5 minutes and let cool.
