Stir the syrup into the puree; pour the mixture into an 8-inch
square
baking dish and freeze until firm, but not frozen. In a chilled bowl, beat the mixture until smooth. Return mixture to pan
and
freeze
for 3 hours.
Let stand at room temperature until soft enough to scoop.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Before serving add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar together.
Press into an 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour, lemon juice, baking powder and salt.
Pour over hot layer.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven.
Cool and then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: clam chowder manhattan style
directions: In heavy soup pot, cook salt pork with onion, parsley and black pepper until pork starts to render fat.
Stir and cook 5 minutes.
Add bay leaf, celery and green pepper; cook 15 minutes. Add juice from minced clams, 1 bottle clam juice, liquid from tomatoes, potatoes and water.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: lemon glazed ham
directions: Bake ham as directed on package.
Combine lemon concentrate, brown sugar and mustard.
Remove ham from oven about 30 minutes before it is done.
Turn oven to 400°.
Score fat on ham and stud with cloves.
Cut 4 to 5 cherries in half and arrange on top of ham.
Brush ham with lemonade glaze.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes longer, brushing occasionally with glaze.

title: creamy green onion spread
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Stir in onions, serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour dip
directions: Combine equal portions of apple jelly and pineapple preserves; mix well.
Add horseradish.
I find that for 2 (8 ounce) jars of apple and pineapple, 1 heaping tablespoon horseradish is about right for me.
Adjust it a little to your own liking.
Wonderful for smoked sausage, ham, meatballs and some cheeses.

title: blackberry dump cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep dish.
Combine into batter flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into middle of melted butter without stirring.
Mix fruit with 1 cup sugar and pour into middle of batter without stirring.
Bake in 350° oven; check after 50 minutes to see if set.

title: pinto bean pizza
directions: Wash off pinto beans.
Let soak in water about 2 hours, then cook in clean water until soft and then drain.
While beans are cooking, shred cheese and slice pepperoni into thin slices.
Also fry up in a skillet your ground beef.
Drain the beef really good. When beans are ready, you use a casserole dish to layer your ingredients.
First put some sauce on bottom of dish, then beans, then pepperoni, then cheese.
Top with sauce and continue. Process until all is finished.
Bake at 350° until all is melted together and hot about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Beat egg, sugar and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Then add zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Stir only until moist.
Bake in muffin cups at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Mix well and boil 20 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: chocolate tea bread
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar and egg in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt in small mixing bowl.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Beat on low speed just until blended; stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: juicy salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and pack into greased and floured loaf pan that holds 4 cups.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until firm and light brown on top.
Loosen sides and let stand in pan for 5 minutes before serving.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix everything together and refrigerate.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: In greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer the first 7 ingredients in order listed. In a bowl, combine the soups, milk and broth. Pour over water chestnuts. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Toss together the butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over casserole. Top with cashews. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Yield: 6 servings.

title: saucy chicken
directions: Combine apricot preserves, dressing and onion soup in bowl. Mix well.
Pour over chicken pieces in large baking dish.
Cover. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 more minutes or until desired brownness.

title: rhubarb custard cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle with rhubarb and sugar.
Slowly pour cream over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown. Refrigerate leftovers.
Great served with whipped cream.

title: spaghetti
directions: Fry the hamburger meat, then boil some water and put the noodles.
Put ketchup and onions in hamburger meat.
Put onions in it.
Let it cook for 10 minutes; cool for a little while where you won't burn your mouth and then eat.
Put salt on it.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; add taco seasoning.
Mix well with all other ingredients.

title: fudgy oatmeal squares
directions: Stir together oats and water. Set aside. In large bowl of mixer, stir together flour, granulated sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. Add shortening, oat mixture and vanilla. Beat at low speed just until mixed. Then mix at medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently. Add eggs. Beat at medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until pick inserted comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack and cool completely. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cut into squares. Makes 24 squares.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Add onion, peppers and meat to bacon drippings.
Brown.
Add rice, bacon, tomatoes and seasoning.
Mix well.
Put in dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: frank-veggie hot pot
directions: Bring broth and water to boil; add macaroni and spices. Return to boil; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in hot dogs, vegetables and onion; simmer 5 minutes longer until macaroni is tender, vegetables are cooked and water is almost absorbed.
Fold in sour cream and mayonnaise if used.
Garnish with parsley, chives and/or green pepper.

title: salsa...mexican style
directions: Slice peppers long ways and place into a saucepan. Just cover with water. Be sure to use a lid because the fumes of the peppers boiling may choke you. Boil until peppers are tender, about 4 to 5 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms and pull out the stems.
Chop stems finely. Heat butter in frying pan and lightly brown the rounded sides of mushroom caps a few at a time.
Set aside.

title: ting a ling cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips in double boiler. After melting, add 2 cups corn flakes.
Stir in until broken up. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour milk, sugar and flour (after mixing
together)	into
melted
butter.
Add peaches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Put slaw mix into medium size mixing bowl.
Drain pineapple, setting aside juice add to slaw mixture.
Add mayonnaise to taste or desired consistency.
Use juice to dilute mayonnaise.
Salt to taste.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown rice in oleo.
Add mushrooms, onions, oregano leaves, beef consomme and water.
Cook, covered, about 30 to 45 minutes until all water is absorbed.

title: chicken vegetable noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken bouillon cubes, potatoes and chicken together until potatoes are still hard.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Add noodles.

title: dad's carrot bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Make a well in the dry ingredients mixture (in mixing bowl) and add nuts, oil, vanilla, sugar, eggs, carrots and optional raisins or coconut. Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Let stand about 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: granny griffin's cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add flour mixture and fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
If using fresh fruit, sweeten to taste.

title: pb & j french toast(6 servings)
directions: Spread peanut butter on six slices of bread, spread jam or jelly on the other six slices of bread.
Put one slice of each together to form sandwiches.

title: fruit salad 2
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: old-fashioned fried chicken and gravy
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Place flour, salt, mustard and pepper in a large paper bag; shake bag to blend ingredients.
Drop chicken in bag and shake vigorously until thoroughly coated.
Preheat oven to warm and place in a large baking dish lined with paper toweling. Heat the shortening or lard in a heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet.
The fat should fill skillet 2-inches.
Add more shortening, if necessary.
Place over moderate heat and when fat is hot enough, start frying chicken.
Start with legs first, as chicken is done, remove from frying pan and place into pan in oven.
Cook all the chicken.
Let chicken remain in the oven while preparing gravy.

title: five-can dump
directions: Mix everything together in casserole; heat in 350° oven 35 minutes.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: low-fat vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of low-fat butter and mix the vegetables, soups, mushrooms and chicken.
Stir up mayonnaise, cheese, broccoli and onions.
Then add melted butter and bread crumbs. Add a little paprika.
Bake at 325° until real creamy.

title: midget mayonnaise cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in large mixing bowl; add vanilla, water and mayonnaise.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rocky road cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 12-inch pizza pan with foil.
Grease foil.
Press cookie dough into bottom of foil line pan.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Sprinkle with peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Drizzle with caramel topping.
Bake additional 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Remove foil and cut into wedges.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine apples, 1 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and granulated sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
In the same bowl combine brown sugar, flour, butter, oleo, remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and salt.
Blend with pastry cutter or two knives until mixed. Spread crumbs evenly over apple mixture and pat down.
Bake 45 minutes.
If top appears to be browning too fast, cover with foil. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli without salt; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; sprinkle with paprika.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300° with lid on.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, milk, baking powder and flour.
Pour into baking dish until dish is 1/3 full.
Arrange peaches on the batter in baking dish.
Combine 1 cup sugar, water and 1 tablespoon of butter; pour over the peaches.
Bake at 350` for 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni with cheese, celery, green pepper, pickles, onion and cucumber in bowl.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar and seasoning.
Mix well.
Chill until serving time.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Layer cranberries, apples and sugar in casserole.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats, pecans and butter in bowl, mixing well. Sprinkle over layers. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Yields 12 servings.

title: jackie's venison chili
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients except for beans. Simmer 1 hour.
Add 2 cans preferred beans and simmer 30 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and chill before serving.

title: cheese savories
directions: Cream together cheese and margarine.
Blend in flour and salt. Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill 2 hours or freeze.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Soften oleo to room temperature.
Combine sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in vanilla and vinegar.
Add coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: creamy nut filling and frosting
directions: Add flour and milk gradually.
Cook to a very thick paste, approximately 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm. Meanwhile, cream shortening with granulated sugar and salt, using mixer on high.
Add lukewarm paste.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in vanilla and chopped nuts on low speed.
Use 1/2 the amount for filling. To remainder:
Blend in up to 1 cup sifted confectioners sugar to make a more generous amount for top and side.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Brown meat in 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat; set aside.

Combine cheeses, sour cream, onion and pepper. In a buttered 2-quart casserole, spread half of the noodles. Cover with cheese mixture, then cover with remaining noodles. Pour melted butter over the noodles.
Pour hamburger mixture on top of the noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cocoa ripple ring
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift together the all-purpose flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk, beating well after each addition.
Spoon 1/3 of the batter into well-greased 6 1/2-cup ring mold or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix presweetened cocoa powder and walnuts.
Sprinkle half over batter in pan.
Repeat layers, ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn out of mold.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this mixture on melted butter.
Do not stir mixture.
Add peaches on top of mixture.
Add remaining sugar over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Easy to make.
Serves 6.

title: chilli
directions: Add a little spaghetti noodles after boiling; boil until done; cook for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with salt, garlic salt and chili powder.
Drain fat.
Add beans and tomato sauce with 2 cups water. Simmer 1/2 hour over low heat.
Serve over rice.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Boil until hard ball stage.
Add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Thoroughly wet a cloth and lay on counter.
Pour the candy on the cloth.
Shape into a log and roll in the cloth.
Let sit overnight or until hard and cloth is dry.
Unroll and slice.

title: brass polish
directions: Mix together into a thick paste, adding water as needed.
Rub onto brass object with soft cloth.
Rinse and rub again to burnish.

title: cheese bits
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add cheese, beating well.
Combine flour, salt and red pepper; gradually add to cheese mixture, mixing well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on baking sheets and freeze until firm.
Place in airtight container and put in freezer.
To serve, place frozen cheese balls on a baking sheet; bake at 400° for about 14 minutes.

title: nut and poppy seed bread
directions: Melt butter in frying pan. Add ground walnuts, sugars and honey.
Slowly add milk.
(Will thicken like a paste; add enough milk so it is easy to spread.)

title: orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° until done.
Cool.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in a large mixing bowl on low speed for 30 seconds; then beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Bake until a wooden pick comes out clean in center in a rectangular pan for 40 to 45 minutes (round pan for 30 to 35 minutes).

title: hard candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until drops of syrup form hard and brittle.
Remove from heat.
After boiling has quit, stir in flavoring.
Pour on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kringlers
directions: Cut edges of bread and roll with rolling pin to flatten. Combine cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar. Spread thickly and roll up. Dip in melted butter and then into sugar combination. Partially freeze. Slice into 5 pieces per roll and refreeze. Bake frozen at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve with sour cream.

title: plum good cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
With electric mixer, blend until smooth.
Pour into greased Bundt or tube cake pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for one hour and ten minutes or until sides of cake pulls away from pan.
Remove cake from pan while still warm.
Frost cake while still warm.

title: bride's rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Add sugar and salt.
Add eggs.
Add yeast to warm water; let set 15 minutes.
Mix together. Add flour.
Knead.
Store in tight fitting bowl and cover.
Let rise.
Make into rolls 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add the carrots (the carrots may be grated in the blender or a meat grinder, but hand grating is the best and it usually takes a one pound package of carrots).
add the flour, salt and cinnamon. Beat the mixture until frothy.
Bake in 8 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cheese snacks(appetizer)
directions: Split muffins.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread on muffins. Broil in preheated broiler until bubbly.
Cut in fourths.
Makes 48 snacks.

title: easy cheesy chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Brown and cook chicken strips in butter until done. Add water, soup and mushrooms. Mix well. Add broccoli and cook until broccoli is done to taste. Serve with white or wild rice.

title: rugelach
directions: The day before baking, mix butter, cream cheese and salt until creamy.
Mix in flour.
Shape into 14 balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: marinara sauce(yield:  3 cups)
directions: 1. In a large skillet, cook the garlic in the oil over medium heat until golden brown.

title: country spice cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Measure in order all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed with mixer until mixed, then beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain and chop.
Melt cheese in mushroom soup and add to broccoli. Saute onion, celery and pepper until tender in the butter and add to broccoli.
Add rice and almonds and place in greased casserole dish.
Put corn flakes on top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling and hot.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan; bring to full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: cool whip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter or margarine and sugar.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add flour and eggs alternately to batter, starting and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings and Cool Whip.
Mix only until blended.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Beat yolks until very light.
Add half the sweetener to whites and half to yolk.
Mix together and beat hard.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Fold into egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into angel food cake pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs in bowl.
Blend bananas and milk in blender.
Mix flours and wheat germ in a bowl.
Next, mix all ingredients together and bake in loaf pan or small loaf pans until bread comes loose from sides.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk custard
directions: Soften butter.
Beat eggs until blended and combine with sugar and flour.
Mix butter, egg mixture and buttermilk.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until knife stuck in the middle comes out clean.
(Cook empty pie shell for 4 or 5 minutes so the bottom won't be soggy.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion in cooking oil.
Season steak as desired.
Add steak and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: peanut butter jumbos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
Cream the butter, sugars, peanut butter and eggs in a large bowl until light.
Blend in baking soda, vanilla and oats until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips and candy pieces.
Scoop out about 1/3 cupful of dough for each cookie. Place on prepared cookie sheets, spacing about 4-inches apart. Press each cookie to flatten slightly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until firm in center.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: rooster stew
directions: In a roaster, saute onions, bacon and sausage.
Do not drain. Add chicken, soup, 1 can of tomato juice, catsup and 1 can of water.
Cook on low heat for about 1 hour. Salt and pepper to taste as it cooks.

title: linda's chocolate candy
directions: In a large bowl, melt almond bark and chocolate chips for 3 minutes. Stir 1 minute until melted and mixed well. Add dry ingredients.
Stir. Turn out on greased cookie sheet or waxed paper. Cool and cut into squares.

title: bananas in sweet-sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add water, vinegar and egg.
Cook until it thickens.
Watch, it scorches easily.
Pour sauce over bananas to coat generously.
Add nuts last.
Store rest of sauce in jar in refrigerator.

title: spinach meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, garlic salt and oats.
Flatten out mixture onto wax paper.
In a small bowl, combine Mozzarella cheese and spinach, saving about 1/4 to 1/2 of the bag.
Add this mixture to center of meat loaf.
Roll sides together and pinching ends to close up openings.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.
Pour 1/2 can tomato sauce over meat loaf and remaining cheese.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion; drain fat.
In bowl, mix soup and milk well.
Spread meat and onion mixture evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour bag of frozen Tater Tots evenly over meat and onion.
Pour soup mixture evenly over meat and potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple sorbet
directions: Puree pineapple and lemon juice.
Add sugar.
Taste and add more as needed.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze for 1 to 2 hours, until just firm.
Place 1/3 into the blender and whirl until smooth.
Put into airtight container.

title: jeweled broaches
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender or two knives until coarse crumbs are formed.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Put in one large bowl.
Refrigerate for at least 20 minutes.

title: chinese chews
directions: Blend dates, sugar, nuts and eggs.
Add, one at a time, 3 rounded tablespoonfuls flour and a pinch of salt.
Shape into balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Place in greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Prick the bottom of pie shell. Bake at 425° for 6 to 8 minutes; cool. Sprinkle cheese and onion evenly into pastry shell. Add cooked broccoli. Combine eggs, half and half, salt and pepper. Mix well. Pour this mixture into pie shell over the broccoli. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 40 minutes, until fork inserted comes out clean.

title: roast wild duck
directions: Rub outside of each
duck
well with oil.
Place celery pieces inside of each duck
and salt and pepper to taste, both inside and out.
Roast in hot
oven
at
for
to
30 minutes; serve 1 whole duck per person.

title: classic 7-up cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Combine butter, shortening, 3 cups sugar and extracts in a large bowl; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Spoon into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef on medium heat, drain and add tomatoes with liquid, chili powder and salt.
Stir well and cook on medium heat until it starts to bubble.
Then turn heat to low, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Then add beans with liquid and bread crumbs; mix well.
Simmer another 15 minutes.
Chili should have thickened.
Serve with crackers or chunks of Cheddar cheese.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together with blender.
Do not melt margarine.
Bake in small muffin tins (mixture is too thick to work
well in large muffin tins) in 350° oven
for
to
15 minutes.

title: light pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt together.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and drop batter onto lightly greased griddle by 1/4 to 1/3 cupful.
Really good!

title: icebox butter rolls
directions: Add 3 cups flour to liquid, then yeast and more flour to the consistency of biscuit batter. Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked pumpkin
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Stir until well blended. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for approximately 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm or cold. Serve with whipped topping.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Step 1:
In microwave saucepan, combine sugar, flour, eggs and milk.
Stir well.
Cook in microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, turning every two minutes, until mixture is thick enough to coat spoon.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Put sugar and water in large iron skillet.
Bring to a boil. Add raw peanuts, reduce heat to medium.
Stir constantly until all liquid is gone.
Pour into lightly greased pan or skillet.
Place in oven at 300° for 20 minutes.
Stir several times.
Let cool.

title: chilli-cheese bake potato
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Heat chilli according to package directions.
Slice open hot potatoes; fluff with fork.
Top with chilli, cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine cheese with milk, butter and garlic salt in saucepan over low heat.
Heat until cheese and butter are melted and blended.
Add drained corn and peppers.
Bake in buttered casserole dish in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: amazingly simple rice
directions: Mix the rice and soups in a casserole dish that has a tight lid.
Put the margarine or butter in the middle; don't stir. Cover and bake it 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mediterranean style chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Spray a 10-inch skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown for 10 to 15 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Add undrained tomatoes, wine, sugar, basil, garlic and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from skillet; keep warm.
In a small bowl, stir together water and cornstarch.
Stir into tomato mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Serve chicken and sauce over cooked spaghetti.
Garnish with olives if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade hot chocolate
directions: Add 2 large tablespoons of cocoa and sugar in pot. Add 1 cup water and bring to a boil. Add condensed milk and 1 cup water. Finish by adding milk. For desired sweetness, add more sugar.

title: coronary cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make cake according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake is done, punch holes in top with straw.
Pour condensed milk and jar of caramel on cake.
Let cool for 2 hours.
Ice with Cool Whip and top with crushed Heath bars. Enjoy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar, flour and chopped pecans.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture and bake for 25 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together eggs, Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Add mixture of flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, shredded zucchini and pecans.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: lemon caesar salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
Run cold water over it and set aside.
In a skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add garlic and basil and saute 30 seconds.
Now add plum tomatoes, chopped or whole, your preference.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add pasta (drained well) and cook, stirring constantly.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Dip wings in 1 beaten egg.
Dip into mixture of 1/2 cup corn starch and 1 teaspoon garlic salt.
Brown and place (single layers in baking dish).
Mix 1/4 cup chicken broth, 1/4 cup catsup, 3/4 cup sugar, 1/2 cup vinegar, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pour over chicken wings.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Turn wings and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: cranberry upside-down muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Spoon 1 tablespoon cranberry sauce into each muffin cup; top each with 1 teaspoon brown sugar.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine milk, oil, orange peel and egg whites; blend.
Add to dry ingredients all at once; stir until just moistened.
Spoon batter evenly over cranberries and sugar in muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 14 to 18 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Loosen edges with knife and invert onto wire rack over waxed paper.

title: "shrimply delicious" shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sour cream, salad dressing mix and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add shrimp and continue beating until shrimp are minced.
If you like a lot of shrimp and larger pieces, add another can and mix well, but do not mince.
Serve chilled.

title: great pecan cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and shortening.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately and beat with electric beater.
Add pecans; bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup and milk together well.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Brown until crisp.
Drain well.
Put soup and milk into crock-pot or slow cooker; mix well.
Add meat balls. Cook on low for 1 hour.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine water, cinnamon and allspice.
Boil.
Remove from heat; add tea bags and steam 8 to 10 minutes.
Strain and remove tea bags.
Add sugar and dissolve; add cranberry juice and lemon juice.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Heat oil and chili powder.
Dip tortillas in hot oil just until soft. Spread with chili.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese. Roll tortilla.
Place in baking dish and put remainder of chili, cheese and onion on top.
Place in a 300° oven to heat and serve at once.

title: mama's pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium size saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring often to prevent sticking.
When cooked, add butter.
Cool and pour in dish or pie shell.

title: no sugar cookies(applesauce)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: delectable cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Next, vanilla and lemon juice.
Fold into prepared crust and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Top with pie filling.

title: summer potato salad
directions: Peel
potatoes; place in large saucepan in salted water and cook
until tender.
Drain and cool completely.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
In
a
large
bowl mix mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish,
parsley,
salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in potatoes and other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: melt in your mouth biscuits
directions: Blend dry ingredients and shortening.
Add milk and egg. Knead slightly.
Roll or pat out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and flour; mix well.
Add enough hot water to make a thick paste.
Warm the milk in a saucepan.	Pour cocoa mixture into milk, stirring until smooth.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until heated through.

title: chili con queso(mexican cheese dip)
directions: Simmer until Velveeta is melted completely.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish; mix soup and wine together. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing on top of soup.
Drizzle melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Blend egg yolks with milk.
Pour into saucepan.
Add crushed pineapple, sugar and vanilla; cook, stirring often.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Prepare a graham cracker crust and pour filling into crust.
Refrigerate, covered with Saran Wrap.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: In large glass bowl, crumble ground beef.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes on High until beef is browned, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.

title: curried rice
directions: Cook rice in broth.
Cool.
Add all the following ingredients. Mix and toss.
Chill and serve.

title: cream cheese pudding
directions: Let cream cheese sit out until room temperature.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and dry pudding, then add in sugar and vanilla.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Before serving, top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: "miracle" chicken 'n noodles
directions: Select a large stewing chicken (or two smaller ones).
Remove giblets and place in large pan; can cut up if desired.
Add enough water to adequately cover chicken; add salt, pepper and seasonings to taste.
Also add a few chopped carrots, onions and celery, etc., according to what you like (onions are also good to add).
Bring to a boil on stove, then turn down to a simmer and skim foam occasionally.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix well.
Add mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add water, nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Saute beef tips on high heat until browned.
Place in crock-pot or large chili cooking pot with 2 cups water.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Cook ground chuck and onion until done; drain.
Add spices and add to beef tips and broth.
Add tomato juice, sauce and beans.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low heat.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix oats, flour and brown sugar together.
Cut in the butter until crumbly.
Place half of this mixture in an 8 x 8-inch greased cake pan.
Cover with the cranberry sauce.
Top with the balance of the oat-flour mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream or your favorite whipped topping.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: In saucepan, mix together fruit, sugar, water and butter.
Set aside.
Mix together remainder of ingredients in buttered baking dish.
Pour first mixture over second.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water; set aside.
Grate cranberries, orange and apple.
Don't peel apple and orange.
Grate rind and peeling.
Add sugar to grated items and mix well.
Mix jello cranberry mixture and nuts together and put in refrigerator until set.

title: chicken
directions: Mix soup, onion, celery and milk; blend.
Salt and pepper the chicken.
Pour mixture into a casserole.
Place chicken on top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat on medium 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch or 3 (8-inch) pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Frost with white or chocolate frosting.

title: lentils colombian style
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, saute lentils and beef in oil for 5 minutes.
Add water and the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer until lentils are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: ice pickles
directions: To cucumbers, add salt and cover with water.
Let it stand for 4 days.
Drain and rinse 3 times.
Add alum, cover with water and let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse 3 times, cover with vinegar and let stand for 10 days.
Drain and add pickling spice and 3 cups sugar.
Add 3 cups sugar the next day and 3 more the next day after.
Heat and pack in jars, if desired.
Will keep just covered in the cabinet.

title: chuck wagon mix
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat; brown the kielbasa and drain excess fat, then return the kielbasa to the skillet.
Stir in the rice, beans and sauce.
Cook over medium-high heat until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: extra-special cream cheese and olives
directions: Blend cream cheese, olives, mayonnaise and sour cream.
When thoroughly mixed, add dash of curry powder; lightly blend. Refrigerate at least 6 hours (best if left at least overnight). Great as a spread on crackers; also makes super sandwich.

title: peanut mounds
directions: Melt together the first 2 ingredients.
Mix together the peanuts, Rice Krispies and marshmallows; combine with melted stars and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: cheregi
directions: Fry in hot grease until golden brown.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount of salted water until tender; drain.
Cook carrots and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Fold in zucchini; put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked deer steaks
directions: Put steaks in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Salt and pepper steak. Cut up butter over steak.
Pour soy sauce over all.
Cover pan with Reynolds Wrap.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: glazed carrots(makes 6 servings)
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the sugar and salt.
Stir and cook for 1 minute.
Add the carrots and stir well.
Add the water and cook slowly until all the liquid has evaporated and the carrots are tender and glazed.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Mix jello and 1 cup of hot water.
Drain juice from pineapple; add the pineapple juice to the jello mixture.
Cut cherries into small pieces.
Add the cherries, pineapple, nuts, Coca-Cola and cream cheese to the jello mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground meat.
Add tomato sauce, water, taco seasoning, beans and chili.
Chop tomato into meat mixture and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Tear flour tortillas in a baking dish. Cover with half of cheese.
Add meat and another layer of cheese. Bake at 350° just until cheese melts.

title: cashew jack "cheese"
directions: Whiz in blender until smooth.
If necessary, you may add 1 to 2 tablespoons additional water or 1/4 cup oil may be added for a more "cheesy" texture.
Blend in lemon juice last.
This cheese is also very delicious on pizza.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour, pecans and sugar. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool completely. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until creamy. Add Cool Whip. Spread over crust, then spread the cherry pie filling over.

title: seasoned dill sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small bowl.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, seasonings, vinegar and butter.
Cook in a double boiler until thick like a custard.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. While cake is still hot, pour pineapple with juice over it. Refrigerate cake until quite cold.
Combine cream cheese, milk and pudding mix and mix well with mixer.
Spread over top of cold cake. Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meats in large skillet.
Drain well.
Add broken up tomatoes, paste, garlic, oregano and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Simmer until consistency of spaghetti sauce (20 to 25 minutes).
Mix cottage cheese and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. (Reserve 1 cup of meat sauce and 1/2 cup of Mozzarella cheese for top of lasagne.)
In ungreased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), alternate layers of 1/3 each of noodles, remaining sauce and remaining Mozzarella and cottage cheese mixture.
Use reserved sauce and cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Serves 8.

title: aunt jill's muffins
directions: Cream the peanut butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and bananas. Dissolve baking soda in hot water, then add to mixture.
Add flour, salt and oatmeal.
Microwave raisins for a few seconds to soften.
Add raisins and mix well.
Bake in greased muffin tin or baking cups for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Put into a bowl; coat with Italian dressing.
Cool pasta.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple with juice and soda; mix well.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix and remaining ingredients.
Add pineapple mixture and blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, finish cooling on rack.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat drippings in skillet.
Add all ingredients to it with 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, over low heat.
Stir occasionally. Crispy = 15 minutes.
Tender = 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly in saucepan.
Heat until bubbly, stirring frequently.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil fryer until tender.
Remove meat from bones.

title: monte's calente chili
directions: Cook beef in skillet until gray in color.
Drain grease off and add remaining ingredients.
Be sure to remove the Japanese peppers before serving.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, brown roast on both sides. Drain fat. Stir in can of mushroom soup, onion soup and 1 cup water. Reduce heat to low. Cook 2 hours. Add vegetables. Cook 45 minutes. Remove roast and veggies. Stir in flour with 1/4 cup water. Cook until thickened.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and spices.
Beat eggs slightly in a separate bowl.
Add pumpkin to sugar mixture; beat and mix well. Add milk to batter.
Add eggs; mix in gently.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: chasen's famous chili
directions: Combine beans with enough water to cover by 2 inches in large saucepan.
Soak overnight.
Simmer, covered, in same water until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Saute green peppers in oil in large skillet over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add onions. Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and parsley. Saute ground chuck and pork in margarine in skillet for 15 minutes.
Add to sauteed vegetables.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add to beans.
Season with cumin, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer; skim surface.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: *To work into a soft dough for kneading.

title: mother's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Cook and drain broccoli.
In a bowl, combine Cheez Whiz, soup and Minute rice.
Add celery and onion and mix.
Stir in broccoli last.
Bake in a covered dish for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Roll slices of dried beef around each half of chicken breasts.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch dish or 3-quart casserole. In a small bowl, combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with almonds and bacon bits.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: raisin oat cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, drop on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350 degree oven.

title: curry cashew stir-fry(lite)
directions: Roast cashews in dry frying pan over medium-high heat until browned.
Set aside.
Place sliced vegetables in pan with 1/4 cup water and curry powder.
Cook over medium-high heat until just limp.
Stir in yogurt.
Top with cashews and serve.
More curry can be used depending on taste.
More nutritious with tofu added.

title: audrey's corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, corn and salt.
Beat eggs and add; add milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Bake in a greased pan at 400° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: party sausages
directions: Use small jars of the mustard and marmalade for small groups and large jars for medium to large groups.
Mix the mustard and marmalade together over low heat.
Use a saucepan big enough to allow room for the sausages.
When the mixture is hot, add sausages.
Use as many as you need, just make sure the mixture covers them all.
Heat thru, stirring occasionally.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers thin.
Wash and slice onions thin. Wash and slice red peppers thin.
Cover with salt and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Mix sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar together.
Pour over cucumber mixture and heat to scalding, but don't boil.
Stir from time to time.
Seal in hot sterile jars.

title: berkley hot spiced cider
directions: Tie cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in cheesecloth or spice holder. Combine with cider and sugar in large saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes, remove spice bag.
Stir in orange and lemon juices.
Heat just until bubbly hot.

title: german chocolate pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake pastry shell 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: pineapple-cheese spread
directions: Beat together pudding mix, cream cheese and drained pineapple. Chill several hours.
Shape into mound on serving plate and press nuts over the spread.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: old fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Chop onions fine. Cook in butter until soft, but not brown. Add bread crumbs, water, celery, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix well.
If not moist enough, add more water or butter.
Makes enough for a 12 to 15 pound turkey.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef with onions and taco seasoning; drain off oil.
Simmer meat, adding kidney beans until slightly soft. Remove from heat and cool a bit.

title: summer fruit pie
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Add Jello and stir until dissolved.
Add bananas, nuts, and strawberries.
Place in pie shell and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pia colada cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cake mix, water, eggs and 1/2 can coconut.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While hot, punch holes into cake.
Pour can cream of coconut over cake; cool. Mix coconut and Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Prepare bottom crust by mixing flour, butter and pecans until crumblike.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15-20 minutes or until golden.
Cool. Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in half of whipped topping. Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Combine vanilla and chocolate pudding mixes and beat in milk until smooth and thickened.
Spread over cheese layer.
Spread remaining whipped topping over top. Sprinkle with grated chocolate candy bar.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender; drain and hold. Add meat to margarine and cook until color changes.
Add salt, pepper and tomato paste; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and drain off fat.
Stir in cottage cheese, sour cream and noodles. Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese
and sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: For best results use green tomatoes that are at
the just before turning pink stage. Cut the tomatoes in 3/8 inch slices. In a large skillet heat the 2 c. oil over medium high heat. In a medium bowl combine egg,

water, 1 Tbsp. oil, salt and pepper. Add 1/2 c. flour, beat with wire whisk until smooth and set aside. In a bowl combine remaining flour and cornmeal. Set aside. Dip green tomato slices, one at a time into egg mixture then into cornmeal mixture coating both sides of tomato. Cook the coated tomato slices a few at a time in hot oil for 4 or 5 minutes or until coating is golden brown. Turn once during cooking. Keep fried tomato slices warm in a 300 degree oven while frying remaining slices. Season to taste.

title: blueberry supreme
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Put half of this amount in bottom of 9-inch square casserole dish.
Cream together powdered sugar and butter.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Pour pie filling over sugar mixture.
Whip Dream Whip and pour over berries.
Sprinkle the other half of vanilla wafers and crushed nuts over Dream Whip.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: filet mignon in wine
directions: Rub filets with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in heavy frying pan.
Add steaks.
Brown on both sides.
Reduce heat to simmer. Add onions and wine.
Cover skillet tightly.
Simmer steaks 3 minutes.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix together; put into greased muffin pans or drop by spoon on baking pan.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: liverwurst pate
directions: I leave meat and cream cheese out to soften awhile.
Then I mash all ingredients together with a hand potato masher and form into small loaf.
Garnish with red onion and parsley.
Serve with crackers for spread.

title: bread stuffin'
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Use to stuff turkey or press into oiled casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raisins, in a large bowl.
Add raisins last.
Bake on cookie sheet in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: orange glaze yams
directions: Cook yams until tender.
Peel and quarter lengthwise.
Arrange in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and sprinkle with salt.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in orange juice and raisins.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook until thick.
Add butter, walnuts and sherry or lemon juice.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Spray 3-quart casserole with Pam.
Drain all fruit, except cranberry sauce.
Mix drained fruit in casserole dish.
Let stand. Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add lemon juice, brown sugar and spices.
Drain excess liquid from casserole.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Pour brown sugar mixture over fruit.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and then refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Blend soup, cheese and egg.
Add mayo and milk.
Stir in broccoli.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Add some buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and shape into balls. Makes 3 balls.

title: granan's hot buttered rum
directions: Cream together all ingredients and store in refrigerator. Into a mug, add 1 tablespoon of mixture, 1 ounce of rum (Captain Morgan spiced rum is especially good) and apple cider (from a market, not bottled apple cider).
Microwave until warm and garnish with fresh lemon slices and cinnamon sticks.

title: golden pork chop bake
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes.
Season to taste. Mix soups and milk and pour over potatoes and chops.
Cover with foil and bake for 90 minutes at 275°.
Take foil off.
Raise heat to 350° for 10 minutes to brown chops.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Beat at least 2 minutes. Bake 35 to 40 minutes (glass) in a 325° oven or 40 to 50 minutes in a metal pan.

title: captain's soup
directions: Mix all together with 1 pound ground beef and 1 onion, chopped and browned.
Simmer 2 hours.

title: faux chicken cordon bleu
directions: Roll with chicken strip in center, then cheese, then ham.
Lay 2 rows of 8 in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring 1 1/2 quart water to boil.
Add broccoli and onions. Boil 10 minutes.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add milk, canned milk and margarine.
Stir until it reaches a boil.
Add thickening.
Get lumps out.
Can be kept warm until served.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bacon and tomato sauce.
Put into a loaf and cover with the bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh stuffed artichokes
directions: Trim the spiny points from the artichoke leaves, using a pair of shears.
Parboil.
Combine mushrooms, shallots, chervil, chives, mushroom soup and liquid beet extract.
Stuff the mushroom mixture between the leaves and over the tops of the artichokes. Place artichokes in a shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until an artichoke is easily pierced through to the bottom.

title: coke salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add both boxes of Jell-O and mix well.
Cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Add Coke, celery and nuts.
Mix well.
Put in container and store in refrigerator. Very good with turkey or serve on lettuce with dab of dressing.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, cornstarch and 1 cup sugar and pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Mix flour, yolks, oleo, baking powder and 1 cup sugar.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Pour over peaches.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place layer of graham crackers on bottom of pan. Make pudding as directed by package.
Mix together Cool Whip and pudding.
Pour over crackers. Place a layer of crackers on top of pudding mix.
Slightly warm icing and spread over crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup sugar and the lemon juice.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Mix lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar; spoon over hot loaf.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: easy cheese hot dogs
directions: With a knife, make slit in hot dogs to within 1/2 inch of ends.
Insert strips of cheese.
Open can of crescent roll dough. Separate triangles (8).
Flatten each triangle a little.
Place hot dog on shortest side of triangle.
Roll up.
Place hot dogs, cheese side up, on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until dough puffs up and turns golden brown.
Makes 8 hot dogs.
Serve with mustard, ketchup, etc.

title: magic rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine or butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine or butter.
Pour condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; chill thoroughly, if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni for 6 to 7 minutes; drain.
Add all ingredients, saving 1 cup of cheese for topping.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: frosty jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in an oblong pan.
Cool cake in pan.
Poke holes in top of cake with fork, close together. Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water and slowly pour into holes in cake.
Refrigerate for two hours.

title: deanna's ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into can and fill with milk until 3/4 full.
Freeze in electric ice cream freezer and enjoy!

title: marinade sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use to marinate beef, venison or other red meats.
Especially outstanding marinade for flank steak.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix bread crumbs with broth. Add remaining ingredients and beat slightly. Pour into greased shallow pan. Bake 30 minutes in hot oven set at 400°. Yields 6 servings.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/4-quart casserole.
In blender, put above items in order listed.
Cover and blend on speed 6 just until potatoes go through blades.
Do not overblend. Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake 1 hour.

title: carrot apple salad
directions: Mix ingredients. Refrigerate. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas in mixer.
Add sugar, eggs and margarine; mix again.
Stir in flour, pecans, baking soda and buttermilk.
Put in greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch pan or 3 small pans and bake at 350° for approximately 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in bread is clean.
Remove from pan and let cool.

title: hot slaw
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in bowl.
In saucepan mix together the vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Pour over the cabbage mix.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine vinegar, egg, parsley, sugar, salt, oregano and onions in a blender.
Blend in oil.
Very good!

title: pecan fingers
directions: Melt butter and add all ingredients.
Shape into fingers and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Children really enjoy these.

title: lemon drops
directions: Peel and slice lemons.
Dip lemon slices in sugar, both sides. Arrange in food dehydrater.
Dehydrate 24 hours or until sugar caramelizes and lemons look fully dehydrated.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix
thoroughly
shortening,	sugar
and
eggs.
Sift together and
stir	in
flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.	Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons
sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased
baking
sheet.
Bake	at
400° for 8 to 10 minutes until
lightly browned but still soft.
(These puff up at first and then flatten out.) Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate and peanut butter cup pie
directions: In blender, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over cold milk and let stand 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low speed until gelatine is completely dissolved (2 minutes).
Add peanut butter and sugar; process until blended.
Pour into prepared crust.
Set on a large plate.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Transfer pie to refrigerator to chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix ingredients and add to starter.
Stir and let set at least 8 hours or until very bubbly.
Take out 1 cup to make bread and refrigerate the rest in a jar with holes punched in the lid until ready to bake again (not more than 5 days).
If not making bread after feeding starter, throw away 1 cup or give a cup to someone. Do not try to build up amount of starter.
Starter must be fed every 3 to 5 days even if not baking.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Cook onion in bacon fat until yellow.
Stir in flour.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Stir in beans gently until heated through.
Serve with crisp bacon sprinkled over top.
Serves 4.

title: "hot" mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown and drain ground chuck, then add the salt and pepper seasoning along with chopped onion.
Cook slowly until ground beef and onion have cooked through.
Pour Crisco in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and heat.
When Crisco is hot, pour about half into cornbread batter and mix, then pour about 1/2 of batter into pan.
Add your ground chuck and seasonings, then add your drained Mexican corn.
Slice Velveeta cheese to cover mixture, then add remaining cornbread batter.
Cook until golden brown. Allow to cool; cut into squares.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and mustard.
Cook whole cauliflower in salted water until crispy-tender.
Frost with cheese mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Put under broiler until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour nuts in pie shell. Mix all ingredients well. Pour over pecans. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Blend cake mix and egg in bowl. Add Cool Whip and mix until well blended. Drop 2 tablespoons batter onto parchment lined or greased cookie sheet, nine cookies at a time. Bake in a 375° oven for 13 to 15 minutes. If you are baking 2 sheets at one time, bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Press on cookies with your fingers to test. If it gives resistance, they are done. Cookies should have the consistency of chewy brownies.

title: dr. pepper baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain liquid from beans and pour beans into baking dish.
Gently
mix in chopped vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour evenly over beans and chopped vegetables which have been mixed with beans in baking dish.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in boiling water.
Soften unflavored gelatin in cold water.
Stir into hot jello.
Add cranberry sauce. Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple.
Sprinkle top with nuts and/or marshmallows, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 5-quart Dutch oven; cook, covered, over medium heat 20 minutes, lifting lid and stirring occasionally.
Yield:
7 cups.

title: more casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion and seasoning until brown.
Drain off fat. Add tomatoes, corn and peas.
Fold in cooked noodles.
Place into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and cheese melts.
Yield:
Serving for 8.

title: breadsticks
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together 1 cup of the flour, the yeast and salt. In another bowl, combine warm water, oil, sugar and egg yolk. Add water mixture to dry mixture. Beat on low to medium speed for 30 seconds, scraping the sides of bowl constantly. Beat on high speed for 3 minutes. Using a wooden spoon, stir in as much remaining flour as you can. Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface, Knead in enough remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic. Cover and let rise until nearly double in size. About one hour. Punch dough down. Cover, let rest for ten minutes. Grease a baking sheet. Divide dough in half. Divide each portion into 8 pieces. On a floured surface, roll each piece into a 12 inch long rope for thin, crispy sticks or into 6 to 8 inch long rope for thick chewy sticks. Place 2 inches apart on prepared baking sheet. Cover and let rise until nearly double. About 45 minutes. Beat together egg white and 1 Tbsp. water until frothy. Brush over bread sticks. If desired sprinkle with seeds or cheese. Bake in a 425° oven about 10 minutes or until golden. Remove from sheet and cool on wire rack. Makes 16 sticks.

title: scallops au gratin
directions: Wash scallops.
Combine crackers (crushed), bread, cheese and some of butter.
Butter casserole and arrange in layers, starting with and ending with stuffing.
Pour milk and rest of melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, milk, sugar and baking powder and pour in pan.
Mix berries, sugar and cornstarch and pour on top of flour mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sunday steaks
directions: Put steaks in flour and brown slightly.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle soup mix on steaks; cover with mushrooms.
Put on onion. Mix beef gravy with water and pour over steaks.
Cover with foil. Bake at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, peanut butter and milk.
Mix
in flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Bake on lightly greased sheets at 350°.

title: sad cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Bisquick and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Add
nuts and coconut.
Bake in a large pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Enjoy.

title: hamburger-onion hoedown
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pastry) in a bowl until well blended.
Make the pastry using a recipe of your choice.
Roll out one half into a 9 x 10-inch shape and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Make six patties of the ground beef mixture and place evenly on the bottom crust.
Roll out the other half of the pastry into a 10 x 12-inch shape and place over the patties, pressing lightly around each one.
Seal edges.
Prick around the patties with a fork and some on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: my mom's refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over 1/2 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons salt and 3 tablespoons shortening.
Cook to lukewarm; add yeast, 2 beaten eggs and 4 cups flour.
Add 3 more cups flour.
Knead until worked into dough.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl; cover and place in refrigerator.
Can keep up to a week.
Shape into rolls. Let rise until double in size, 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Also can be made into cinnamon rolls by rolling into rectangle.
Spread with butter and brown sugar.
Roll like jelly roll.

title: daddy's big pot of chili
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain grease. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in order given, cutting in shortening as you normally do for biscuits or pie dough.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly. Turn dough out on floured board and knead lightly.
Pat out and cut.
Place on a greased baking sheet. Let dough rise slightly. Bake at 400° until lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: In a medium size baking dish, add tuna, soup, noodles, peas, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well, then top with rest of cheese. If desired, place crushed potato chips on top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: durkee vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla and butter flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
(Use high speed with electric mixer.)
Sift flour and salt together.
Then add slowly.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into 10-inch stem pan that has been well-greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and cut in cubes or shred in food processor.

title: stuffed baked pork chops
directions: Slit pocket lengthwise in middle of unboned or meaty side of chop.
Brown onion and celery in fat.
Add salt, pepper, sage, poultry seasoning, bouillon cube and water.
Stir to dissolve cube.
Add bread crumbs.
Stuff each pork chop with 1/4 of mixture.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Cover.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes more to brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scotcheroo bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Add cereal and mix well.
Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together over hot, but not boiling, water.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat and spread over bars.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: theresa shea's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Wash red sweet potatoes and boil with skins on for 1/2 to 1 hour, depending on how many.
Cook until firm, not overcooked. Cool and peel while still warm.
Slice and place in ovenproof dish (melted margarine in bottom).
Spoon melted butter on top of each slice and then cover each slice with dark brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 hour to 1 hour (makes as brown as you want).
Serve to hungry guests who say, "Um Um good!"

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dessert pecan cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until they bubble.
Mix baking powder, flour and nuts.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Mix in nuts.
Fold in egg white and nut mixture into yolks.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Cook in oven at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with whipped cream.

title: quick and easy bean and sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Pour everything into Dutch oven (except rice). Taste as you mix seasonings in until you get it to your taste. This does not take long to cook, just heat everything up.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Pour mushroom soup into small casserole dish. Follow with green peas (drained).
Combine water chestnuts, pimento and chopped onion; pour over peas.
Mix crackers, Cheddar cheese and melted margarine; pour onto other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and put into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in 1 1/2 cups water until tender.
Drain vegetables, saving 1 cup water.
In saucepan, melt 1/2 stick butter.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add 2 cups milk; stir until creamy.
Add 4 slices of cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted over medium heat.
Add vegetables to sauce; stir, then add clams.
Do not drain juice.
Pour clams and juice into sauce.
Add 1 cup water that you saved from vegetables, stirring constantly until mixture is blended to a smooth consistency. Serves 4.

title: venison over rice
directions: Tenderize venison by marinating in buttermilk for several hours.
Remove from marinade but do not scrape off or blot dry. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dredge in flour and saute in hot oil until browned but not done.
Remove from fire and drain on paper towels.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in saucepan until tender; drain.
Melt cheese with milk in saucepan.
Stir in flour, mixed with a little water. Cook until thick.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
In greased casserole, layer macaroni, cheese sauce and ham.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry kiwi mock margarita
directions: PLACE water, orange juice, lime juice and drink mix in blender container; cover. Blend until drink mix is dissolved.
ADD ice; cover. Blend on high speed until smooth.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Wash and place potatoes in a large kettle. Cover with water and boil until skins crack. Boil eggs for 15 minutes; place in cool water to cool. Peel when cool and chop into 1 /2-inch pieces. In a large mixing bowl, combine vegetables, eggs and apple.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan; bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to butter and marshmallow mixture.
Press into pan lined with wax paper; refrigerate.

title: sue's jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in two cups of boiling water.
Add orange juice and 1 can of water.
Blend in softened cream cheese and fruit. Chill in mold.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Line 9-inch pan with pastry. Brush the inside with egg whites. Chill. Beat eggs slightly with fork; add the sugar and salt. Stir until blended. Add milk and cream; blend well. Gently pour into pie crust. Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and continue to bake for 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt, pepper, garlic powder, onions and chopped green pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: texas chili-cheese dogs
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese; melt.

title: german potato salad sauce
directions: Mix together cornstarch, water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook several minutes.
Add to bacon and simmer until glossy.
Add water if necessary to make enough.
Can be cooked in microwave.
Enough for 3 to 4 pounds of salad potatoes, sliced.

title: pipe down pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes into 9x13 casserole dish.
Season pork chops to taste and brown in skillet.
Place chops over potatoes. Combine soups and pour over chops.

title: surprise casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slightly cook peas and carrots.
Then layer on top of beef.
Pour gravy over this.
With three potatoes, make mashed potatoes, slightly firm. Cover meat and vegetables with mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix lettuce, pepper, onions, beans and pimentos together. Just before serving add grated cheese, crushed Fritos and Catalina dressing.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 3 thin layers and ice each layer with the following icing.

title: fluffy tapioca pudding
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: easy cookies(for kids to make)
directions: Chill and roll out dough.
(May use cookie cutters.)
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; make hole in center.
Mix liquid ingredients with spoon.
Add to dry ingredients and stir.
Spray pans. Pour and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° (two 9 x 5-inch pans for 1 1/4 hours or four 2 x 5-inch pans for 1 hour).

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes, omitting salt.
Stir in dressing mix and margarine, if desired.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until done in large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Stir in green beans, tomato soup, water, salt and pepper.
Put meat mixture into a 1-1/2 quart casserole dish.
Cook potatoes in boiling salt water in a covered pan for about 20 minutes or just until tender and drain.
Mash the potatoes while hot and blend in egg.
Add enough milk to make potatoes fluffy yet stiff enough to hold their shape.
Season with salt and pepper. Drop potatoes in mounds on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4-6.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and margarine; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat for 6 minutes.
Gradually blend in 3 cups of flour on a low speed, then beat on high speed for a couple of minutes.
Add the whipping cream and flavoring; beat a few more minutes.
Pour into a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rich man's fudge
directions: Combine sugars, butter, milk and salt and bring to soft ball stage (238°), stirring often.
Remove from heat; blend in chocolates, marshmallow cream, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
When firm, cut into squares and dip in white chocolate dip.
Makes about 60 pieces.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries and sugar in 4 cups water until berries pop open. Mash with potato masher and add jello. Let cool.
Cut all fruits and nuts very fine; add to berries. Add nuts. Pour in dish or mold and refrigerate.

title: beef stew(it's delicious - you should try it!)
directions: You can add anything you like on your pizza.

title: creamy three-meat casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and soup.
Wrap chicken pieces in slice of beef.
Place in shallow casserole and dot with bacon strips.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Do not cover.
Bake at 200° for 4 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars.
Add egg and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flavoring.
Sift flour, measure and sift with salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful on oiled cookie sheet. Bake in moderate oven about 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet, heat 1 Tbsp. oil. Add chicken and cook until browned. Add soup, 1/2 c. of water and vegetable combination. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cracker jack
directions: Mix butter, sugar, salt and Karo.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and baking soda.

title: elegant wedding cake
directions: Bake 2 (12-inch) cakes (Duncan Hines white cake mix) as directed. Cool. Frost with can of cake frosting. Use whipping cream, then add coconut.

title: orange yogurt fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken and rice in casserole or pan.
Spoon the soup over all.
Add water, salt and pepper.
