Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream cheese grapes
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and mayonnaise, beating until smooth.

Add grapes to cream cheese and stir gently just until coated. Spread pecans on a large sheet of waxed paper. Roll the cheese-coated grapes in the pecans until well coated. Place grapes in a baking sheet and chill at least 1 hour.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
May top with canned cherries or other fruit.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, egg, onion, salt, and pepper and shape into balls.
(Should make approximately 60)
Mix the chili sauce, lemon juice, and grape jelly and heat.
Drop meatballs into simmering sauce and cook until done.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peas, beans, corn, onion, celery and pimiento.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients; heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 10-12.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add garlic powder.
Add water and bouillon cubes; bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until noodles are almost done.
Add chopped broccoli and cook 5 minutes. Add milk and Velveeta cheese.
Simmer until all the cheese is melted.

title: cucumber relish(canning recipe)
directions: Combine cucumbers and salt and let stand 1 hour.
Drain overnight.
Next day, grind together celery, peppers and onions. Make syrup of vinegar and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add ginger and turmeric, then add all ground vegetables.
Bring to boiling point, stirring occasionally, but do not boil.
Pack into sterilized jars.

title: steak roll ups
directions: Cut steak into 1 x 2-inch pieces; roll in bacon (hold with toothpicks).
Roll Steak Roll Ups in flour; fry until light brown.

title: christmas scent
directions: To make your house smell festive throughout the holidays, mix the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and turn back to simmer.

title: coke chicken
directions: Mix together the ingredients and cook on top of stove until done, about 35 to 45 minutes over medium heat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and bananas alternately in small amounts.
Bake in greased pan 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sour cream topping(this is another good cream topping.)
directions: In a saucepan, mix and heat, over medium heat, all ingredients.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and let cool.
Spread on cake, then add pie filling on top, such as cherry, peach, apricot, apple, blueberry or pineapple.
Also, this is good topped with fresh strawberries.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Brown sausage, crumbling with a fork.
Saute onion and add to sausage.
Add peas, water, tomatoes and sauce.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot over rice.

title: barbecue sirloin pork
directions: Cut steaks into 1-inch long strips.
Mix together the barbecue sauce and jam.
Marinate strips in sauce mixture all day. Brown in skillet (about 4 minutes on each side).

title: mississippi mud sauce
directions: Combine 1/3 cup marshmallows, cocoa and cornstarch in a small saucepan. Gradually stir in milk and corn syrup. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and cinnamon.
Let cool.
Stir in 1/4 cup marshmallows and Grape-Nuts.
Serve over frozen yogurt, angel food cake or fresh fruit.
Yields 1 cup, 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: stuffed dates(watschke's fruit appetizer)
directions: Slice an opening in each date with a knife.
Fill the date with almond butter and place 1 whole almond on top.

title: pocketbooks
directions: Combine mixture (meat, milk and seasonings).
Cook meat mixture, pepper and onion in frypan.
Drain off excess fat.
Add pimento and soup.
Stir to blend.

title: yummy fudge cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips in a large bowl (by hand). When thoroughly mixed, fold in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by tablespoonfuls approximately 2 inches apart onto a cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican casserole
directions: When Rice-A-Roni gets to "add 2 cups of water stage", add ground beef and stewed tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes.
Add grated cheese and olives.
Put in oven and melt.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in 2-quart bowl and cover with enough milk to go 1/2-inch from the top of bowl.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and sugar. Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: decorator's frosting
directions: Gradually add milk and shortening to confectioners sugar in large bowl.
Mix on low speed until mixture stays together.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes, until thoroughly mixed.
Decrease mixer speed to low and add flavorings until thoroughly distributed.

title: potato stir-fry
directions: Cook potatoes and rosemary in oil for 7 to 8 minutes, using skillet, until potatoes are crisp and golden brown.
Add pepper. Cook 2 minutes.
Add peas, mustard and salt.
Cook over medium heat 2 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Cut vegetables in 1-inch pieces and cook each separately until tender.
Drain all vegetables and discard all water except celery and onion water (save 2 cups).
Make a syrup with vinegar, sugar, water, spices, cinnamon and left over celery, onion water.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pack mixed vegetables in sterile jars and pour syrup over to 1/2 inch of top of jar.
Cold pack 10 minutes for pint jars.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand in refrigerator at least 6 hours before serving.
Best to make a day ahead.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Combine and put in container for 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in tube or Bundt pan.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix well, dip hot dogs.
Deep fry until desired doneness.

title: worlds most delicious cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars, add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, except pecans, mix until combined.
Stir in pecans.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts, place on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not over cook.
Allow to cool a few minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in bag and coat 1 can of biscuits at a time.
Grease Bundt pan and arrange biscuits evenly.
Melt 1 cup sugar, 3/4 cup butter and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate.

title: frozen cantaloupe(dietetic)
directions: Cube cantaloupe and place in freezer container.
Cover with pineapple.
Freeze.
Thaw partially before serving.
Yield: 1 serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift 4 cups flour with the sugar and soda.
Cut in Crisco until it looks like cornmeal.
Place in an another bowl 1 cup flour, buttermilk and yeast dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix well to the first mixture and place on a floured paper and roll wet.
Place in a greased covered bowl and keep in refrigerator and cook as you need.
Roll out like biscuits.
Cook at 425°.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour orange juice into a measuring cup add rind and melted shortening and enough water to make 3/4 of a cup.
Combine orange juice mixture and beaten egg.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and nuts and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Let stand for 20 minutes before baking.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Turn the potatoes into a large bowl and mash smoothly.
Add the pineapple, nutmeg, salt, brown sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Mix with a fork until all are combined.
Turn into a shallow baking dish and spread evenly.

title: lemon delight
directions: Make pie crust following directions on the box.
Spread in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Chill evaporated milk overnight.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add honey, lemon juice and rind.
Fold in whipped evaporated milk.
Spread the mixture over the crust.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: caramel baked apples
directions: You will need one regular size (10 x 16-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Mix the margarine, 1/3 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and the flour until crumbly and pat into a 9-inch or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Raise edges about 1 1/2-inches.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, the egg and vanilla; spread on pastry. Slice the apples and toss with 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange over cream cheese mixture and top with the sliced almonds.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and 400° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Wilton Chocolate:
Melted
chocolate over warm water or in microwave, then dip on waxed paper.
Form balls and cool.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Blend sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients with milk; beat well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Fold in blueberries that are slightly moist and have been floured with about 2 tablespoons flour saved from the flour.
(Flouring the blueberries keeps them from sinking to the bottom of the pan.)
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: microwave stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix and stuff green peppers. Pour spaghetti sauce over top. Bake 20 minutes in microwave.

title: strawberry tapioca
directions: Bring water to boil, then add tapioca.
Boil gently, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from stove then add jello, sugar and strawberries.
Cool in refrigerator.
After it sets up a little, fold in Cool Whip.
Enjoy!

title: chicken delight
directions: Place
broccoli
in
bottom
of casserole.
Add chicken which has been cut into bite size pieces.
Make sauce from the milk, soup, lemon juice, salad dressing and curry powder; pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Beat egg whites; add sugar and almond extract.
Crumble crackers and add to dates and nuts.
Fold crackers, etc.
with egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until straw comes out clean.
Serve topped with whipped cream and cherry.

title: bavarian creme dessert
directions: Mix
margarine, flour and pecans and spread in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 - 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake 6 sweet potatoes.
Peel and mash while warm.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one yolk at a time.
Beat well. Add mashed potatoes, coconut and nutmeg.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mix well, but stir lightly.
Put into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: kidney vegetable salad
directions: Combine in appropriate size bowl the corn, beans, pepper, onion and tomatoes.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in grated zucchini.
Sift remaining dry ingredients and add to egg mixture, stirring well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Mix sugar in to taste. Spread on bread or serve with crackers.

title: potato bread
directions: At night, make a sponge of the first 5 ingredients.
Cover and let stand overnight in warm place.
In the morning, add to the sponge the remaining ingredients.
Mix and knead to medium stiff dough.
Let rise until doubled.
Shape in loaves or rolls.
Let rise until doubled again.
Bake from 40 to 60 minutes in moderate oven at about 400°.
Cool on rack.

title: great cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixer.
Spoon out on ungreased cookie sheet, allowing room for dough to spread.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cookies will be soft and limber while hot, but will crisp up as they cool.

title: candy apple walnut pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts, cinnamon candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into 1 frozen pie crust.
Break or crumble second pie crust into very small pieces; toss with remaining 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in preheated oven at 375 on a preheated baking sheet 55-60 minutes until candies melt and bubble up through crumbled crust.
Cool completely before serving.
Makes 8 Servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 round layer pans.
Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on high, scraping occasionally for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake oblong pan 60 to 65 minutes or layers 50 to 55 minutes; cool.
Frost with Butterscotch Meringue.

title: spring sunshine pie
directions: Mix cold water and cornstarch until smooth.
Combine hot water and sugar and bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Cook about 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks. Return to mixture and cook a few minutes longer.
Add lemon juice. Cover and set aside.

title: deviled hash
directions: In large heavy skillet, cook beef and onion over medium-high heat, stirring to break up meat, until beef is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, scraping up browned bits in skillet.
Cover, simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over fluffy mashed potatoes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grate vegetables, then mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs and cheese.
Put into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend the first two ingredients together and then gradually add the juice.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: frittata
directions: Remove casings from sausage and brown in olive oil in skillet. Break up sausage.
Drain and reserve.
Saute onions and mushrooms.
Add drained, chopped spinach and saute 1 minute more. Remove and combine with sausage.
Butter 9-inch square pan. Combine next 6 ingredients.
Mix well with vegetable sausage mixture.
Pour into pan and top with remaining cheeses.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: popovers for 2
directions: Mix ingredients with wire whisk until smooth.
Grease small (custard) Pyrex dishes.
Divide dough between 3 dishes.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.
Do not open oven.
Reduce heat to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Put eggs in double boiler.
Add vinegar and sugar, beating constantly, until thick and smooth.
Remove, then add butter.
Let cool.
When dressing is cool, fold in marshmallows, fruits and whipped cream.
Chill 24 hours.
Substitute other fruits if you wish.

title: chili
directions: Fry ground meat and onion until lightly browned.
Add rest of ingredients and slowly boil 45 to 60 minutes, adding the beans the last 5 minutes.

title: frozen delight
directions: Grease mold with butter or oil.
Beat together the cream cheese, pineapple, strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in mold or deep loaf pan and freeze.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grits souffle
directions: Add grits to boiling water and cook gently until done.
Add salt and butter; mix well to melt butter.
Thoroughly mix eggs with milk.
Add a little of the hot grits to egg-milk mixture; return mixture to hot grits and mix.
Stir in grated cheese.
Put mixture into greased baking dish and bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 minutes, or until browned on top and a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Place liquid in percolator.
In the basket, break up the cinnamon sticks and add cloves.
Perk.
Makes 8 cups.

title: dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Add green onions with tops sliced finely.
Add dill weed and garlic powder and mix thoroughly.
Serve with raw vegetables (carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, celery, etc.).

title: hot chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cheese in saucepan.
Heat on warm setting until cheese is melted, 25 to 30 minutes.
Blend thoroughly and serve warm with corn chips.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Butter toasted bread.
Cut toast into cubes and place into pan. Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Thoroughly beat eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Pour mixture over toast and let stand for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining 4 teaspoons of sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over bread.
Place dish into shallow baking pan.
Pour hot water into pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake 1 hour. Remove dish from water.
Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 8.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine in glass bowl in microwave on High for about 30 seconds.
Stir in flour to form smooth paste.
Stir in milk gradually.
Microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes on High; stir once during cooking.
Stir in cheese until melted and smooth.
Pour over fresh or steamed vegetables.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplant and slice in thin slices.
Beat eggs with 1/2 cup of water.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture and then breadcrumbs.
Fry in small amount of oil until lightly browned on both sides.
Drain well on paper towels.
Spray a 12 x 14-inch baking pan with Pam. Place a layer of eggplant.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Continue layering until all eggplant is used. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbling, about 1 hour.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Mix soy sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic, green onion and ginger root; place in a plastic bag with the chicken pieces.
Close bag tightly and marinate for 5 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade and place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour, basting one or two times with marinade.
(The Japanese marinade serves to tenderize the chicken as well as impart a delicious flavor and moistness.)
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Heat
12 ounces Coke to boiling point.	Dissolve jello. Stir. Add
remaining Coke, plus the cold water.
Chill.
When mixture is	soft
set
add cherries, pecans and marshmallows. Mix gently. Garnish with whipped cream if desired.

title: chocolate halfway bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Mix shortening, white sugar and 1/4 cup brown sugar until creamy. Add egg yolk, water and vanilla; mix well. Thoroughly mix in flour mixture. Pat into dish. Top with chocolate chips. Beat egg white until stiff, then gradually beat in 1/2 cup brown sugar. Spread over chocolate chips. Bake until done, about 25 minutes. Cut while warm. Cool in pan.

title: aunt gladys carter's pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes without opening the door.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat for four minutes.
Dough will be stiff.
Fold in sour cream and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a tube pan.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Add remaining batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: frosting for fresh grapefruit cake
directions: Cook together sugar, egg whites, corn syrup, salt and juice for 7 minutes or until stiff peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add grapefruit peel and vanilla.
Beat 1 to 2 minutes, until frosting is thick enough to spread.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; add taco seasoning.
Mix as instructed on package.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix salad and vegetables. Just before serving, toss meat mixture, salad vegetables, cheese, crushed Doritos and salad dressing.

title: tomato and chive soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Saute onions, carrots, leeks, garlic and curry powder over medium heat until vegetables are soft, but not brown.
Stir
in flour and tomato paste. Immediately reduce heat; stir in chicken broth, tomato juice, wine, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly 1 hour.
Strain soup if desired.

title: snowball cake
directions: Remove all brown from cake.
Pinch cake into tiny pieces.
Set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons of cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water, pineapple juice and pineapple, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until mixture is partly congealed.
Whip 2 packages of Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold in gelatin mixture.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: In large saucepan, mix tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer about 2 hours.
In mixing bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onions and olive oil.
Shape into balls and cook about 1/2 hour.
Add to sauce mixture and cook 1/2 hour more. Serve over spaghetti.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Saute onions and green chilies in oleo.
Mix soups, milk, chicken broth and bring to a boil, then add onion and chilies.
Slightly crush Doritos.
Spread 1/2 the bag in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 soup mixture over chips; then 1/2 chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat same order, ending with cheese.
Bake 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: easy pecan "sticky" buns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small pan, combine syrup, margarine and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil and simmer for two minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch round or square pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Open crescent roll packages; do not unroll dough.
Cut each package into 8 pieces.
Place in rows in pan (flat like regular cinnamon rolls). Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes; invert on serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: microwave new england clam chowder
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine potatoes, celery, onion, reserved clam liquid, salt, parsley, thyme and pepper.
Mix well. Cover.

title: rocky road peanut butter popcorn bars
directions: Place popped popcorn and raisins in large bowl. In saucepan, heat corn syrup and butter to boiling. Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter pieces and peanut butter. Stir until smooth. Pour mixture over popcorn, tossing gently to coat all pieces. Press into buttered 9 inch square baking pan. Sprinkle marshmallows and peanuts over top, pressing lightly into popcorn mixture. Melt combined chocolate chips and shortening over very low heat. Drizzle over top. Cool several hours before serving. Cut into 2 1/4 x 1 inch bars. Makes 36 bars.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze as directed.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Mix everything together in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish. Save a few Tater Tots for top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Add Tater Tots the last 15 minutes on top.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: miracle whip devil's food cake
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and sugar.
Add flour and cocoa sifted together.
Add warm water with soda added to it.
Mix ingredients well and bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: party beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles in a saucepan as label directs; drain and rinse. Put oil, onion, beef, salt, pepper and thyme in a large skillet. Cook until meat loses its color but is not browned.
Combine soup and milk.

title: baked dried corn
directions: Grind corn in the blender.
Combine corn and hot milk.
Let stand 1 hour; add eggs and rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a casserole and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: squash and chicken medley
directions: In large frypan (pot), place oleo and melt over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, turning about 10 minutes or until brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Place yellow and zucchini squash and onion in pot and stir about 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pot.
Add tomatoes, then sprinkle with spices.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Serve hot with rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie shell as directed and cool.
Mix 3 tablespoons peanut butter with powdered sugar slowly (with fork).
The peanut butter will bead up. Sprinkle peanut butter beads on bottom of pie shell. Pour prepared pudding in the shell.
Sprinkle more peanut butter beads on top of pudding. Whip egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and vanilla.
Spread meringue on top of pie, then sprinkle more peanut butter beads.
Place under broiler until top is light brown.
Serves 8.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, lightly beaten egg and vanilla to the melted butter.
Add the liquid to dry ingredients and put into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
In sauce pan combine peppers, soup, enchilada sauce, and Milnot.
Heat slowly, then mix with hamburger meat.
In large casserole pan alternate meat mixture with cheese and chips.
Save half the cheese and put on top just before taking from oven.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat ingredients to dissolve cranberry sauce.
When dissolved, add meatballs, then bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cut zucchini and onion and put in a little bit of water and boil until tender.
Then put in blender or mash with potato masher.
Add chicken broth and potato soup.
Mix together, then add sour cream.
Whisk sour cream in mixture.
Eat as a cold soup or warm.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, lemon pudding, eggs, Crisco oil and water.
Beat at moderate speed for 5 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
While baking, mix orange juice, powdered sugar and Crisco oil.
When cake is done, prick cake all over with a large fork to bottom of cake.
Pour mixture over hot cake.
Delicious and moist.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Cook chicken and vegetables, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until chicken is almost done.

title: depression cake
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until raisins are tender; cool. Sift together the next 6 ingredients; add to raisin mixture.
Add the vanilla.
Grease and flour a 9-inch square or a loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes for square pan or 75 minutes for loaf pan.

title: sinful sesame cookies
directions: Line a cookie sheet with graham crackers separated.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes the butter, margarine and sugar.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts and sesame seeds.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Put on wax paper immediately to cool.
Not too fattening.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper and remove.
Brown meat in same pan.
Heat soup, tomato sauce and water.
Mix everything together. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375° and bake for 35 to 40 more minutes.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips or cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stack-up
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain. Add beans, onion, tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings and allow to simmer on low setting. While this is simmering, prepare rice as directed on package. Serve each in separate containers the meat, cooked rice, onion, lettuce, tomato, cheese and picante sauce.
Put broken chips on plate.
Add meat, then rice, onion, etc., stacking each on top. Finish with cheese and picante sauce.
Great for family get-togethers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fold corn into beaten eggs.
Add cornbread.
Mix into egg mixture, then add sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
If using onion and bell pepper, saute in oleo and add.
If not, then just add melted oleo.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients; spoon into pie crust. Cover with second crust. Crimp edges to seal and slit top of crust. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Spread evenly on 1 package of English muffin halves. Freeze 30 minutes. Cut each half into 6 pieces and freeze in plastic bag until ready to use. Broil until brown on top.

title: chocolate cake with fudge icing
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa; add water in large saucepan.
Take off heat.
In large mixing bowl, mix flour and sugar.
Pour cocoa mixture over dry ingredients.
Beat, then add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Mix well; pour into greased 12 3/4 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare frosting about 5 minutes before cake is done.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs. Beat well. Stir together flour and baking soda. Add alternately with topping to butter mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into squares.
Makes about 24 brownies.

title: chocolate crispy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Stir in cereal and bits. Drop onto greased sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook the ingredients until thick; pour over vanilla wafers and bananas which have been placed in a long, large glass dish.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, margarine and chocolate chips.
Mix in cereal and stir until coated.
Put powdered sugar in a brown bag; add cereal mixture and shake until well coated.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook until forms a hard ball in water.
Beat and pour in buttered pans.

title: double crust apple pie
directions: Combine all the above ingredients (except apples) and heat to boiling point in heavy pan on top of stove.
Then pour over apples in pan lined with unbaked crust.
Add top crust.
Seal and bake at 400° to 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, salt, crushed pineapple, banana and enough red food coloring to give a pink tint.
Lightly fold in nuts and cherries.
Spoon into fluted muffin cups which have been placed in muffin pans.
Freeze.
Cover with plastic wrap and store in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving to loosen paper cups from pan.
Peel off paper cup and place on salad greens.
Fills 12 large muffin cups.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt oleo with cocoa and water. Let come to a boil; pour over sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon. Then mix with buttermilk; add eggs. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple and juice and soda.
Mix well.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and remaining ingredients.
Add pineapple mixture; blend.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.

title: fried ripe plantains
directions: Peel the bananas and cut diagonally approximately one-half inch thick.
Place the oil in a frying pan (or a deep fryer). Allow the oil to get hot; you should see some bubbles, but not smoke.
Place the plantain sections into the oil and cook on both sides until golden light brown in color.
Place on a paper towel to blot excess oil.
Serve hot.
Serves six.

title: cheese-garlic rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and drop by large spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
melt butter and add remaining ingredients. Brush butter mixture on rolls.
Bake at 400 until done, about 10-15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add all other ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool and spoon mixture on buns (kaiser or hamburger).
Add 1 slice Mozzarella cheese on top of mixture.
Wrap sandwiches in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Drain peaches; dice.
Add enough water to peach juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Stir together pudding and gelatin; add liquid. Cook and stir to a full boil.
Chill.
Blend in prepared Dream Whip and diced peaches.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all
dry ingredients together.
Dissolve soda in warm water; add alternately with mayonnaise and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven about 40 minutes or until cake springs back when tested.
Use two 9-inch pans or a tube pan.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix ingredients together. Roll out and cut noodles in strips. Good for in soup.

title: jellied fruit salad
directions: Stir gelatin in boiling water until well mixed.
Add fruit liquid or water; add lemon juice (if used).
Chill until partly firm.
Stir fruit into mixture.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in given order.
Dip with ice cream scoop.
Press down to flatten.
Bake 12 minutes for soft cookie or 18 minutes for hard cookie.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen 9-inch cookies.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut cream cheese into chunks.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low 4 hours. Stir and serve.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large sauce pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using buttered spatula, press into buttered 13 x 9 inch pan.
Cut when cooled.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour 1/4 c. cooking oil in baking pan; let heat up in oven while mixing ingredients.

title: mahone bay steamed brown bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Add the rest.
Pour into greased molds, filling 2/3 full.
Steam 3 hours.

title: white confetti fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt white chocolate with milk; remove from heat.
Stir in salt, vanilla and cherries.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Turn onto cutting board.
Cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.

Drain. Arrange 4 noodles in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook onions in margarine until tender; blend in cream cheese. Stir in cottage cheese, egg, basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; spread one-half of mixture on top of noodles.
Combine soup, milk and wine; stir in shrimp and crab.
Spread one-half of soup/shrimp mixture over cottage cheese layer.
Repeat layers; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with American cheese and bake 2 to 3 minutes more.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Garnish with tomato, parsley and shrimp.

title: stuffed chicken surprise
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese and softened cream cheese together.
Fold in scallions and mushrooms.
Spread mixture on chicken breasts. Fold in half and secure with toothpicks.

title: mini-applesauce muffins
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Add dry ingredients gradually and mix well.
Fold in nuts or raisins. Grease small muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Just before serving, dip top of muffins in melted butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Use reserved 1/4 cup flour to coat fruit and nuts.

title: creamy hot chocolate
directions: Heat milk in microwave on High approximately 4 to 5 minutes. Add powder mixture to milk, halfway between heating time and stir. When heating is finished, add caramel and ice cream.
Use a hand blender and beat lightly to cream.
Pour into mugs and drink. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy cherry cheesecake
directions: Combine softened Cool Whip and cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and smooth out. Place in refrigerator to chill 2 hours.
Pour cherry Comstock over cream cheese.
Can serve immediately or chill until ready to serve.

title: grilled vegetable marinade
directions: Mix well and pour over mixed vegetables.
Marinate several hours.
Grill until vegetables are tender.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream sugar and
oleo.	Add beaten eggs.
Mix flour and soda together and add
to sugar.
Add bananas and nuts and mix well. Spoon into muffin pans sprayed with Pam.
Fill 3/4 full in each muffin.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: quick chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in hot oil.
Add remaining ingredients (except rice).
Cook for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for at least 1 1/2 hours until firm.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Bake 15-20 minutes at 350.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions until tender, but still firm.
Drain.
While noodles are cooking, melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add heavy cream and cook over medium heat. Reduce heat to low and add sour cream, stirring constantly.
Do not allow cream sauce to boil.
Toss noodles, cream sauce, Parmesan cheese and chives until well blended.
Serve immediately. Yield:
6 servings.

title: vegetable potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in boiling water and cook until tender, 10 minutes or so.
Drain well.
Combine all other ingredients, except paprika, in a large mixing bowl.
Toss lightly.
Spoon into a serving dish.
Sprinkle with the paprika.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Roll on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 minutes.

title: apple cranberry bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the eggs, sugar and oil.
Combine the flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture just until combined (batter will be very thick).
Stir in apples, cranberries and nuts.
Transfer to baking pans, 8 x 4 x 2 or little pans, whatever you prefer.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix sugar, water and oleo.
Cook until comes to boil (don't boil). Combine in blender with dry milk.
Blend until smooth. Refrigerate until needed.
Makes 1 cup.

title: spinach casserole 2
directions: Thaw spinach, press out water.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: my mother's cornbread recipe
directions: Mix together and beat.
Bake in large baking pan (approximately 12 x 14-inches) at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.
Butter the top and serve in squares.
It's almost like dessert!

title: strawberry pie
directions: Let pie shell cool.
Combine ingredients except fresh strawberries.
Bring to boil.
Let cool.
Add strawberries; mix well.
Add to cooked shell.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until jelled.

title: pound cake
directions: Before you start, sample the rum and check quality.
Good, ins't it!!

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Place hash browns in 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with bread crumbs and top with melted butter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel candy
directions: Melt white chocolate (microwave or saucepan).
Add pretzels and nuts.
Place wax paper on a cookie sheet; spread mixture onto sheet.
Place in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Break apart and store in refrigerator.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon in pot that you make your chowder in.
Crumble bacon in pot.
Put all ingredients, except clams and clam juice, in pot with bacon and cover with water (just so you can see it).
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add clams and clam juice to cooked vegetables and cook for 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Makes 12 quarts.
Can be used immediately or freezes well.

title: cookie monster(makes over 100)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large pan; cream well.
Add eggs, vanilla and syrup.
Beat well.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or less; don't get too brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan and bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour chocolate mixture slowly into the syrup mixture, blending well.
Very slowly pour eggs in, stirring constantly, to mix well.
Add vanilla and pecans.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cook hamburg and drain.
Shred lettuce; add tomatoes, onion, green and red pepper, hamburg, cheese and 3/4 of the bag of Doritos (rolled into crumbs).
Add the dressing and stir until the dressing is well mixed.
Top with remaining Doritos.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Pour boiling water over broccoli; let drain.
While this is draining, saute onions and celery in the butter.
Cook rice in water until done (according to directions).
Mix all together; place in buttered baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Don't cover.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in large chunks.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Bake 40 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; stir in next 5 ingredients.
Heat until bubbly; pour in casserole.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Keep popcorn warm in 250° oven while preparing coating.
In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans or roasting pans.
Bake in 250° oven 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Break apart.

title: black-eyed pea supper dish
directions: Cook sausage, breaking into pieces.
Drain fat.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Stir well.
Add black-eyed peas (drain first).
Cover and simmer slowly for 15 to 20 minutes or until desired consistency is reached.
Pour in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Warm in oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
This is great to make ahead, because it lets the flavors blend.

title: wine jelly
directions: Mix wine and sugar in top of a double boiler.
Place over rapidly boiling water, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and, at once, stir in pectin. Pour quickly into hot sterilized glasses.
Skim, if necessary. Cover at once with 1/2-inch hot paraffin.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet dough
directions: Mix together and raise for about 1 1/2 hours, doubles in size.

title: aunt hilda's brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and Crisco well.
Add sugar (mix brown and white sugars together).
Beat real well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at least 1 per minute.
Add flour and milk alternately. Stir in flavoring and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Turn to 325° and bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open oven door until cake has baked at least 1 hour.
(May need to be cooked 15 minutes longer.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown sausage and spread over bread (drain off grease).
Put cheese on top.
Beat eggs and mix in salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over other ingredients.
Add milk and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and mix.
Pour over popped corn.
Put in shallow baking pan or cookie sheet.
Put in oven at 200° for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In large saucepan, bring pineapple and syrup to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk.
Fold in whipped topping and pecans.
Pour into an 8 cup mold.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: company cake
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Sift flour, cinnamon and sugar together.
Add oil and eggs.
Beat thoroughly for 4 minutes on medium speed or 300 strokes by hand (almost too thick for mixer).
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla. Pour in pan.
Bake 1 hour or until springs back when pushed down (maybe more).
Can be covered with 2 packages of butterscotch morsels.
Let them bake on top of cake, or make glaze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble crackers in a baking dish.
Put remaining ingredients in dish.
Use the rest of crackers on top and bake at 375° until brown.
